Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.00,0:00:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}压制：{\r}Ξ血龍吟д  {\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}字幕：{\r}天羽 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.81,0:00:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本人董建华，谨此宣誓\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I, Tung Chee Wah, do solemnly swearto serve as the{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.31,0:00:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本人就任中华人民共和国香港特别 行政区行政长官\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administration Region (HKSAR) of the People's Republic of China,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.42,0:01:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并当拥护中华人民共和国香港特别 行政区基本法\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and to support the Basic Law of the HKSAR of the People's Republic of China,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.63,0:01:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,效忠中华人民共和国香港特别行政区\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and swear allegiance to the HKSAR of the People's Republic of China,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.26,0:01:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽忠职守、遵守法律\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to perform my duty to the best of my ability and obey the law,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.57,0:01:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,廉洁奉公为香港特别行政区服务\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to honestly serve the HKSAR,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.74,0:01:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中华人民共和国、中央人民政府\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}responsible to the Central People's Government,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.48,0:01:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和香港特别行政区负责\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}the People's Republic of China and the HKSAR{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.46,0:01:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,董先生（香港特别行政区首长）\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr Tung (Chief Executive of the HKSAR),{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.79,0:01:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些少年犯犯案时还很年轻， 心智未成熟\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}these juvenile offenders were very young when they committed their crimes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.33,0:01:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是他们的刑期却比成年犯还要长\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yet theirterms were more severe than those for adult criminals{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.50,0:01:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是吗？粱议员，怎么你不早来找我？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Really, Councillor? Why didn't you let me know earlier?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.51,0:01:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实他们每个人都写过信给你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In fact each of them wrote to you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.71,0:01:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过可能你太忙，没时间处理\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You were probably too busy to deal with it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.61,0:02:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我自己也写过三封信给你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I wrote you three times too{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.02,0:02:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们从没有放弃过自己， 而且每个人都很有上进心\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They've never given up on themselves. They are all very industrious{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.75,0:02:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你帮帮他们减刑，给他们一个机会 重新做人吧\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Help them to remit their sentences; give them a chance at a new life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.89,0:02:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有权减刑的吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Do I have the right to remit sentences?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.13,0:02:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基本法第四十八条，写明我们的 特首是有权的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Article 48 of the Basic Law states that our Chief Executive has the right{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.23,0:02:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,李国能（香港终审庭首席大法官） 是个好法官\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Andrew Li (Chief Justice of the Court of Final Appeal) is a good judge,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.44,0:02:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在法律界有很高声望\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and has a high reputation in the realm of Law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.71,0:02:28.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,市民也很满意他当香港终审庭 的首席法官\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}People are delighted he is the Chief Justice in the Court of Final Appeal{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.58,0:02:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他所建议的刑期，我可以改吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Can I change the sentences he handed down?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.68,0:02:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们有没有宗教信仰？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Are they religious?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.72,0:02:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有宗教信仰还好一点\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It would be betterforthem if they are{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.29,0:02:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最少精神有寄托\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That they at least have some mental support to cling to{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.09,0:03:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1985年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Year of 1985{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.82,0:03:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,机灵点好不好？说好去偷铜嘛！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Be smart, won't you? We're supposed to be stealing copper!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.46,0:03:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绳子也不带一条，你怎么做事的？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You didn't even bring a rope; what's the matter with you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.80,0:03:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这个老大怎么带小弟的？！真没用！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How did you become the chief, huh? Useless!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.27,0:03:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老大！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Chief!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.04,0:03:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么事？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.94,0:03:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Look!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.48,0:03:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老大，铜这么重！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Copper's so heavy,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.51,0:03:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不如去抢劫！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}why don't we just go and rob them?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.52,0:03:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好呀！老大\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah! Chief!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.28,0:03:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有意思！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why not?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.27,0:03:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,搞定了那妞！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We fixed that chick!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.20,0:04:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快跑！跑呀…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's go! Run...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.02,0:04:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈妈，我约了同学去看电影， 我现在出去了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom, I'm going to a movie with my classmate, I'm going now{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.79,0:04:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你早点回来呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Be home early!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.33,0:04:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}OK!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.44,0:04:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,誉玲，你干什么？鬼鬼祟祟的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you doing, Yue-ling? So sneaky!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.54,0:04:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,藏著些什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you hiding?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.15,0:04:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是你的？！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Is this yours?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.99,0:04:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能穿校服去的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't go in my uniform{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.65,0:04:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我穿校服去看电影，同学会笑我的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They'll laugh at me forthat{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.86,0:04:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怕被同学笑你？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Is that what you're worried about?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.36,0:05:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好好的校服你不穿，你穿这个， 干嘛妖里妖气的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You don't want your uniform; all you fancy are cheap dresses like this!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.90,0:05:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像个飞女一样！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}And you make yourself look like a street kid{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.90,0:05:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不怕被人强奸吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Aren't you worried about getting raped?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.77,0:05:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怎么会给你穿？！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't let you wear it!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.40,0:05:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我剪烂它！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I must cut it up!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.34,0:05:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放手…放手\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let go! Let go!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.41,0:05:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这个死丫头，我这么辛苦把 你带来香港\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Damn you! I spent so much effort bringing you to Hong Kong{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.88,0:05:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我日日夜夜干活\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I work like a dog{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.28,0:05:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你居然不给我好好的读书\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yet you don't like school{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.75,0:05:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这死丫头，你要把我气死了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You damned girl, you really drive me nuts{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.26,0:05:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将来还有什么希望\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You damned girl, you really drive me nuts{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.73,0:05:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宝马山今晨发现双尸命案\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Two bodies were found this morning in Braemar Hill{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.93,0:05:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一对外籍男女被发现倒毙在草丛中\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Aforeign couple was found dead in the bushes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.67,0:05:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是你要带我来香港的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It was you who brought me to Hong Kong{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.07,0:05:41.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还说这里是天堂\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You said this was paradise{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.07,0:05:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我每天上课，都被人家在叫我“灿妹”\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}People call me country girl in school{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.44,0:05:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里没有一个是好人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}People here are bad,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.64,0:05:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连你也是一样！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}including you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.31,0:05:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出去买酱油都让我穿校服\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I even have to wear my uniform to go to the corner store{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.76,0:06:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁呀？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Who is it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.69,0:06:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿琼，是我呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's me, King!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.99,0:06:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟你在同一生产线工作的那个呀\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We worked on the same assembly line{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.66,0:06:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么事？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What do you want?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.13,0:06:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿琼，他是粱先生，她是张小姐\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is Mr Leung, King! This is Miss Cheung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.80,0:06:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们正在帮助我们的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He's helping us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，厂方很刻薄我们\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The factory is very mean to us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.50,0:06:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你明天跟我们一起罢工吧\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why don't you go on strike with us tomorrow?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.64,0:06:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在没有上班，已经是罢工了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I have stopped work, this is a strike{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.84,0:06:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,工人的权益应该靠工人自己去争取\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Workers should fight forthemselves{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.14,0:06:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,呆在家里不上班\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The factory and society won't understand exactly what you need...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.78,0:06:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,厂方跟社会根本不会明白 你们究竟需要些什么\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}when you just stop going to work{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.62,0:06:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果钟表厂所有的工人 都出来静坐抗议\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The factory wouldn't dare to exploit your rights...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.99,0:06:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,厂方就不敢胡乱的剥削 你们应有的权益\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}if all watch workers made a sit-in protest{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.62,0:06:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿开它…我怕呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Take it away! I'm scared!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.43,0:06:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别怕！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't worry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.23,0:06:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,捉紧袋口就行了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Just hold the bag tight{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.51,0:06:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,待会带你出去玩好吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you want me to take you out to play?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.05,0:07:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好呀！我要去海洋公园、去看电影、 去滑冰\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah! I want to go to Ocean Park, to a movie and skating{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.15,0:07:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,行…行！去哪儿玩都行\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Fine... fine! Whereveryou want...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.29,0:07:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要你乖乖的听话就行了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}as long as you're good{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.74,0:07:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,表姨父，我觉得全香港只有 你一个人对我好\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You're the only person in Hong Kong who's nice to me, uncle!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.78,0:07:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你听话，我对你会更好\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If you behave, I'll treat you even better{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.32,0:07:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么你的内裤这么大的？！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why are your panties so big?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.43,0:07:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我哪有自己的内裤啊\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't have my own underwear{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.70,0:07:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是穿别人的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They are somebody else's{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.03,0:07:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你乖的话，我改天买些新的给你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll buy you some if you behave{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.14,0:08:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,午间新闻：较早前在宝马山发现的 双尸案死者\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Good afternoon, police confirm that the couple found dead in Braemar Hill...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.81,0:08:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,警方已经证实为英童学校的预科生\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}were Form 6 students at an English Foundation School{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.51,0:08:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,父母是在香港工作的英国人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Their parents are British, working in Hong Kong{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.05,0:08:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当他们知悉儿女遇害的消息\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}After learning the news,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.95,0:08:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女死者的母亲当场晕倒\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}the dead girl's motherfainted,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.65,0:08:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,男死者的父亲情绪激动\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and the dead boy's father was very angry{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.52,0:08:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杀害我儿子和他的女朋友的人 应该被判死刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Whoever did this to my son and his girlfriend deserve a death penalty{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.69,0:08:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们的行为连禽兽也不如\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They'd be put to death, they're animals, they shouldn't be walking around!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.79,0:08:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,香港到处都是坏人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Villains are everywhere in Hong Kong,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.66,0:08:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们这些成年人也经常受人欺骗\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}even adults are always getting taken{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.00,0:08:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你乖的话我会很疼你的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll treat you very nicely if you're a good girl{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.61,0:08:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的事你千万不要告诉金姨\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't tell Aunt Kim about us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.85,0:08:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果金姨死了， 你会不会对我好一点？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Will you treat me better if Aunt Kim dies?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.33,0:08:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果金姨死了， 你会不会对我好一点？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Will you treat me better if Aunt Kim dies?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.90,0:09:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果金姨死了， 你会不会对我好一点？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Will you treat me better if Aunt Kim dies?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.01,0:09:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果金姨死了， 你会不会对我好一点？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Will you treat me better if Aunt Kim dies?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.86,0:09:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从来没有欢呼声加冕 勤劳未可得到幸福\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}There have never been cheers of support, Hard work has not brought happiness{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.83,0:09:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,浮沉在社会底处 历尽了压迫心不死\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Floating at the bottom of society, the heart didn't die of countless woes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.37,0:09:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,埋藏在我心中的激愤 犹如睡醒的母狮\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The anger in me... is like a lioness woken from sleep{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.41,0:09:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同行在抗争的火线 命运已紧紧结连\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Walking the picket line together, ourfates are tied{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.26,0:10:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,作战同往这一刻 青山、海、与天\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The moment we're fighting the battle together, the green mountain, the sea, and the sky{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.66,0:10:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在世界画上这一笔 欢呼响震天\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is the mark we leave in the world. The cheers shake the sky{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.93,0:10:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的膀胱有病嘛\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My bladder has problems{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.74,0:10:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个该死的组长一天只许我上两次厕所\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That goddamned group leader only lets me go to the washroom twice a day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.51,0:10:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实这次的罢工\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In fact this strike{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.21,0:10:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在近几年香港的工人运动来说， 是一次突破来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}is a breakthrough forthe workers' movement{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.28,0:10:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在很短的时间内 已经召集了很多工友\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We recruited many workers forthe sit-in protest{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.38,0:10:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在工厂门口静坐抗议\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}in a very short time{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.78,0:10:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反对厂方各种不合理的待遇\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We object to the very unjust rules in the factory{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.19,0:10:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,埋藏在我心中的激愤 犹如睡醒的母狮\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The anger in me... is like a lioness woken from sleep{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.56,0:10:41.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同行在抗争的火线 命运已紧紧结连\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Walking the picket line together, ourfates are tied{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.07,0:10:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,作战同往这一刻 青山、海、与天\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The moment we're fighting the battle together, the green mountain, the sea, and the sky{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.58,0:10:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在世界画上这一笔 欢呼响震天\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is the mark we leave in the world. The cheers shake the sky{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.80,0:11:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，没有提及我们的新闻啊\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Our protest is not mentioned,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.77,0:11:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全都是宝马山的双尸案\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung, only the Braemar Hill couple{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.37,0:11:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都刊登在主页头条呢！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}All the front-page headlines are taken{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.24,0:11:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的没有我们的新闻呀？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}There is really nothing about us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.88,0:11:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你找清楚了没有？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Have you read them thoroughly?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.01,0:11:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的看清楚了，你看！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, I did!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.00,0:11:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,张有铭，十六岁\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Cheung Yau-ming, aged 16,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.04,0:11:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被控于一九八五年四月十七日\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}was charged with killing the British couple, John McBrady and Helen Hayes...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.84,0:11:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在宝马山杀害英籍男子约翰麦伯迪\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}in Braemar Hill on April 17, 1985. The accused is guilty of murder...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.31,0:12:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,及英籍女子海伦希斯\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}in Braemar Hill on April 17th 1985.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.22,0:12:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谋杀罪名成立\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The accused is guilty of murder.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.85,0:12:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于你还未成年，本席判你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Since you're not an adult,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.15,0:12:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“等候英女皇发落”\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}you are to be detained at Her Majesty's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.70,0:12:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1997年——回归前6个月\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Year of 1997, 6 months before Handover{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.02,0:12:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别哭！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't cry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.79,0:12:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再哭就喂你吃屎\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll feed you shit if you do!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.76,0:12:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别再哭！再哭我真的会给你吃屎\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop crying! I'm really gonna feed you shit if you don't!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.76,0:12:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再哭？就打死你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll kill you if you don't stop!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.17,0:12:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,张有铭，我是你在公开大学的同学 张誉玲\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Cheung Yau-ming, I'm Yue-ling, your classmate at the Open University{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.97,0:13:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在学生报读到你的文章\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Having read your article in the student press,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.38,0:13:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得你的文字很生动\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I find your language very lively{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.55,0:13:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知何故，我幻想你是 一个弹钢琴的人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know why I imagined you were a piano player...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.42,0:13:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很想写封信给你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and wanted to write you a letter{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.49,0:13:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是当我查到你地址的时候\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}When I found out your address{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.39,0:13:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我才知道你原来是一个囚犯\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I realised you were a prisoner{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.73,0:13:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我参加散文比赛输给你的时候\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}When I lost to you in the prose competition,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.90,0:13:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我又再次拿你的文章来看\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I read your article again{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.00,0:13:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,忽然间，我很想更了解你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Suddenly, I wanted to know more about you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.07,0:13:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很冒昧的写了一封信给你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I only sent you an unsolicited letter{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.27,0:13:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想不到，你很爽快的给 我一个见面的机会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't expect you'd be willing to meet me so quickly{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.58,0:13:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,探监吗？那边去！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Jail visit? That way!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.19,0:13:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请出示身分证\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Your identification card, please!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.96,0:13:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你来看谁的？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Who are you visiting?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.23,0:13:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,张有铭\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Cheung Yau-ming{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.13,0:14:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知不知他的编号？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you know his number?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.74,0:14:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有一些书是给他的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I brought him some books{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.95,0:14:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这本硬皮书不能带进去\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hard-cover books are not allowed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.62,0:14:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}OK!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.10,0:14:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,领回你的身分证\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Here's your identification card!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.43,0:14:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.70,0:14:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些东西都不能拿进去， 你放进十三号储物柜里\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}None of these are allowed. Put them in locker no. 13{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.67,0:14:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.15,0:14:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把身上的金属物品放下\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Leave all metal stuff here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.26,0:15:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,举起双手，高一点…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Raise your hands. Higher!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.77,0:15:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,行了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}OK!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.80,0:15:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿回钥匙吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Take your keys back!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.97,0:16:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是张誉玲呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm Cheung Yue-ling!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.31,0:17:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是张誉玲\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm Cheung Yue-ling!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.62,0:17:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你来看我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Thanks for coming to see me!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.59,0:17:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实我早就想来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I wanted to come long ago{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.99,0:17:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过早阵子很忙\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But I was very busy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.93,0:17:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不是香港人？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You are not a local?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.00,0:17:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我十多岁的时候跟我妈妈 从大陆来了香港\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I came from the Mainland in my teens, with my Mom{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.17,0:17:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我曾经很努力的学习广东话\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I once tried very hard to learn Cantonese{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.54,0:17:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想像一个香港人嘛！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Because I wanted to be like a local!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.64,0:17:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是现在我觉得不用了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But now I find there's no need{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.98,0:17:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想像我自己就行了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}ljust want to be myself{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.35,0:17:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都是中国人罢了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We are Chinese, after all!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.92,0:17:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你会听普通话嘛？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So do you speak Potunghua?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.56,0:17:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你翻译的题目选什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What topic did you choose fortranslation?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.16,0:17:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法律\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.13,0:17:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法律？！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Law?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.73,0:17:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听到法律就害怕了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I feel a chill in my bones whenever I hearthe word{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.47,0:18:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没办法了，我们在这里每天 都会接触到法律\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't help it! We come across it here every day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.92,0:18:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难怪很多监友都说\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}No wonder a lot of my friends here say...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.46,0:18:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们两母子每次见面都像 拍悲情电影一样\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}that every mother-and-son meeting is like a tragic movie{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.86,0:18:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你呢？你跟你家人见面的时 是演“喜剧”的吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What about you? Is it a comedy when you and yourfamily meet?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.34,0:18:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在这儿已经十二年了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I've been here for 12 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.84,0:18:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的家人从来没有来过看我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My family never came to visit me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.15,0:18:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想，他们\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I think, they...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.15,0:18:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已经忘了我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}already forgot about me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.59,0:18:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你什么时候出狱呀？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}When will you finish serving yourterm?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.97,0:19:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起！誉玲\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sorry, Yue-ling!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.74,0:19:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不太会说话\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm not very talkative{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.81,0:19:11.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对著我那半个小时，是不是很闷呀？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Was it boring to spend 30 minutes with me?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.15,0:19:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实在你来之前的几天\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In fact, I started practising talking to myself...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.78,0:19:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就开始跟自己练习说话\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}a few days before you came{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.72,0:19:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自从十六岁我进来以后\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ever since I came here at 16,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.72,0:19:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就一直没机会跟女性说话\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I have never had a chance to talk to women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.69,0:19:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我觉得这不是最重要的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But I don't think this is the most important thing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.56,0:19:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我心里只是惦念著我的家人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Because I often miss my family very much{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.66,0:19:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在见到你以后，我忽然间想起 一件事情\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}After meeting you, I suddenly think that...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.97,0:19:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的家人可能已经忘了我了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}my family might have forgotten about me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.64,0:19:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是，我现在还是很记得 我亲生妈妈是什么模样的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But I still remember what my natural mother looked like{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.75,0:19:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,誉玲，我不是你幻想中那个会 弹钢琴的人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yue-ling, I'm not the piano player of your imagination{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.45,0:19:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我懂得把你的样子记下来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But I know how to make a drawing to rememberyourface{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.32,0:19:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那天你问我什么时候可以出狱\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That day you asked me when I would finish serving my term{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.13,0:20:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一时之间我真是不能回答你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Out of the blue, I really couldn't answer{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.96,0:20:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我是被判等英女皇发落的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Because I am detained at Her Majesty's pleasure,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.57,0:20:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是到现在，我还没有刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I haven't been sentenced{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.47,0:20:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发仔…发仔\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Fatt... Fatt{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.81,0:20:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.87,0:20:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的英文好，不如你写信给英女皇吧？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Your English is good, why don't you send the Queen a letter?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.84,0:20:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你以为“等候英女皇发落”\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You think detained at Her Majesty's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.95,0:20:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是真的要英女皇来判案吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}really refers to the Queen?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.98,0:20:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要囚禁多久\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The length of our jail terms depends on{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.95,0:20:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是由彭定康（香港总督）决定的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Chris Patten (Governor of HK){\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.45,0:20:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,铭仔，牙膏还给你！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yourtoothpaste, Ming!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.39,0:20:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在石壁监狱里\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In Shek Pik Prison,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.13,0:20:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有几个像我一样\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}there are several others detained at{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.30,0:20:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被判“等候英女皇发落”的犯人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Her Majesty's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.63,0:20:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最近我们这帮等候发落的犯人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Recently, prisoners like us, detained at Her Majesty's pleasure,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.97,0:20:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给殖民政府几个部门踢来踢去\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}are being bounced between departments of the colonial government{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.97,0:20:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们很担心，英国人离开香港以后\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Afterthe British leave Hong Kong, we are very worried about...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.38,0:20:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将来的特区政府会怎样处置我们…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}what the SAR government will do with us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.78,0:20:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们很希望政府在回归前\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So we really hope our sentences{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.12,0:21:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以给我们一个确定的刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}will be set before the Handover{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.79,0:21:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要让我们无了期地等下去\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}And we'll not be kept waiting for ever{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.96,0:21:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要不然，我们的命运真的不知会怎么样\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Otherwise we really don't know what ourfate will be{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.37,0:21:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还记得寄了几封信吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you remember how many letters you sent?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.01,0:21:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寄了一百多封，政府拿我们当皮球踢！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}A hundred-odd letters, the government kicks us around like footballs!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.08,0:21:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寄了有什么用？！一点作用都没有\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What's the point? It's no use at all!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.68,0:21:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,外面正在搞回归（英国人把香港 主权交还中国）\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Handover (HK returns to China) is approaching{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.21,0:21:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁会管我们！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Who'll care for us?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.28,0:21:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,67544，有人来看你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}67544, someone is paying you a visit{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.34,0:21:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什么可以帮忙的？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}May I help you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.34,0:21:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好！我找粱忠勤议员\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hi! I would like to speak to the Councillor, Leung Chung-ken{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.31,0:21:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生在开会，请等一下\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He's at a meeting, please wait for a while{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.54,0:21:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.51,0:21:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，有人找你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung, someone is here foryou{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.68,0:22:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道了，谢谢！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}OK, thanks!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.05,0:22:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，十楼太低了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The 10th floor is too low, Mr. Leung{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.75,0:22:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,替我想一想办法再高几层\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Can you help me to get several stories higher?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陈先生，粱议员当时帮你搬 上楼已经不容易的了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Getting you moved in was already difficult, Mr. Chan!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.06,0:22:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在上了楼，你又嫌太低\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Now that you have, and you find the level too low{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.99,0:22:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你自己到房委会重新申请吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Go apply again to the Housing Authority yourself!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.76,0:22:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，你的职员怎么这样子？ 我可投了你一票的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How can your member of staff say that, Mr. Leung? I voted foryou{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.33,0:22:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陈先生晚上要上班，白天想安静的睡觉\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Chan works at night and wants some quiet sleep in the daytime{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.80,0:22:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们该体谅他的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We should understand that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.34,0:22:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么说就对了，我没白投你的票\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That's the point! My vote is worth it!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.27,0:22:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，B座粪渠堵了很久了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Councillor, Block B's pipes are still blocked,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.77,0:22:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,何时帮我们修？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}when will you help us?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.91,0:22:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会叫房屋署跟进的了，放心吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I will ask the Housing Department to follow up. Don't worry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.24,0:22:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的，谢谢你！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}OK! Thank you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.48,0:22:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了，时间差不多了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}OK, time is running out{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.91,0:22:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员还要开会，你们回去等消息吧\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Councillor has a meeting to attend, we'll get back to you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.75,0:22:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会跟进的，放心吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll follow up, not to worry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.82,0:22:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你们！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.09,0:22:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，全靠你了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung, I depend on you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.39,0:22:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放心吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't worry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.26,0:22:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.96,0:22:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好！你是不是粱先生？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hi! Are you Mr. Leung?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.76,0:22:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的！什么事？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes! How can I help you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.86,0:22:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这封信是我朋友托我交给你的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My friend wants me to give you this letter{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.16,0:22:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Fine!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.54,0:22:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我好像也收过一封\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I seem to have received a copy too{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.41,0:23:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些人现在很害怕九七年 后的法律衔接问题\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}These people are worried about legal problems after 1997{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.61,0:23:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,政府到现在都没给他们确定的刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}And the government hasn't yet given them determinate sentences{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.58,0:23:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这封信我看过的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I read it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.75,0:23:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,写来写去都是什么不人道、 不公平或不合理等等\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's all about inhumanity, injustice, intolerance, all that jazz{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.92,0:23:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是他们都是杀人犯呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But they are all murderers, after all!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.23,0:23:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们也知道自己该受惩罚\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They should have known they would be punished{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.06,0:23:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是犯人也是人嘛！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But prisoners are humans too!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.27,0:23:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果把他们无限期地关押下去\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's inhumane...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.17,0:23:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也是不人道的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}if they are detained indefinitely{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.70,0:23:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且国际人权法庭也裁定\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}And the International Court of Human Rights also ruled that...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.77,0:23:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无限期押后判刑是违反人权法的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}indefinite detention violates the law of human rights{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.61,0:23:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们没有刑期的吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't they have a term?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.81,0:23:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“他们被判的是““等候英女皇发落“““\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They are detained at Her Majesty's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.75,0:23:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“本来““等候英女皇发落“““\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Detained at Her Majesty's pleasure...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.12,0:23:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是给那些心智不成熟的青少年犯 有改过自新的机会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}primarily gives mentally immature youngoffenders a chance to correct themselves{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.65,0:23:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是政府到现在还没有 给他们确定刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Since the government still hasn't defined theirterm,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.92,0:23:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么等候英女皇发落就 变成了无限期坐牢\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}detained at Her Majesty's pleasure has turned into indefinite imprisonment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.16,0:23:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有的人已经关押了二十年， 还不知道自己的刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Some have been detained for 20 years and yet still don't know theirterms{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.53,0:23:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全香港有多少个这种犯人？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How many prisoners of this kind are there in Hong Kong?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.13,0:24:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,二十三个！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}23!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.73,0:24:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，青衣（香港社区之一） 有二十三万人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Tsing Yi (a Hong Kong community) has a population of 230,000, Mr. Leung{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.54,0:24:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，我这里有一份资料，你看看\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Take a look at the information I've got here, Mr. Leung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.84,0:24:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些都是香港重犯的记录\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}All these are records of serious criminals in Hong Kong{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.64,0:24:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些抢劫银行，杀了警察的成年重犯\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}These adult criminals robbed a bank, and killed a cop{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.11,0:24:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最长判了四十六年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The longest they got was 46 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.45,0:24:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,扣了假期、假释等等\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}After deductions of holidays and parole,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.72,0:24:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们实际上只须服刑二十三年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}actually they only need to suffer punishment for 23 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.62,0:24:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是那些心智不成熟的青少年犯 却无限期给关押著\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But those young offenders are detained indefinitely{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.63,0:24:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有，粱先生，你看这案子！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Also, look at this case, Mr. Leung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.50,0:24:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,八七年元朗的一宗械斗案， 法庭判了谋杀罪\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The court judged an armed fight in Yuen Long in 1987 to be a murder case{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.43,0:24:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一被告给判了死刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The first accused was sentenced to death{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.50,0:24:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是成年犯，其他三个少年犯…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But he was an adult offender; the other 3 young offenders...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.41,0:24:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给判的是“等候英女皇发落”\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}were detained at Her Majesty's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了九零年，同案的成年犯 获得港督特赦\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In 1990, the adult offender in that case received the Governor's amnesty...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.35,0:24:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,改判二十五年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and was sentenced to 25 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.01,0:24:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,扣掉三分之一假期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}After deducting 1/3 of it for holidays,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.78,0:24:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个成年犯的实际刑期只有十八年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This adult offender's actual term was 18 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.89,0:24:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已经快出狱了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He will soon be released{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.59,0:24:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是当年被他操纵的孩子已关押了十年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But the kids under his control have been detained for 10 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.86,0:25:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到现在还不知道自己的刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and yet still don't know about theirterms{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.59,0:25:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭，你快去叫所有等候发落的犯人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming, call all the detainees as soon as possible,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.60,0:25:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他们通知自己的家人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}notify theirfamilies...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.57,0:25:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在星期日到粱忠勤的办公室开会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to meet in Leung Chung-ken's office on Sunday{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.64,0:25:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没想到你会帮我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't expect you to help{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.74,0:25:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实我只是一个犯人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm just a prisoner{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.62,0:25:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没坐牢以前只是一个小混混\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I was just a street kid before coming here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.05,0:25:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你别这么说自己嘛\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't say that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.26,0:25:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在孤儿院长大的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I grew up in an orphanage{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.76,0:25:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,九岁那年，爸爸和后妈把我接回家\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}At nine, Dad and my stepmothertook me home...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.60,0:25:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原来是为了申请大一点的廉租屋\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}just so they could apply for bigger housing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.24,0:25:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后来后妈生了三个孩子\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Then my stepmother gave birth to 3 children{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.11,0:25:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一家六口\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In a family of 6{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.05,0:26:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,家里天天吵个不停\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}there were fights at home every day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.29,0:26:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道是不是那时候我太小了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Maybe because I was too young{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.76,0:26:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赚不到钱，帮不了家里\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I couldn't make any money to help them{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.37,0:26:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们就把我赶了出来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}so they kicked me out{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.08,0:26:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实我这辈子的愿望就是 要找到我的亲妈\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The hope of my life is to find my natural mother{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.92,0:26:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我爸爸只会骂我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My Dad scolded me...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.05,0:26:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也不对、那也不对\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}forthis and that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.69,0:26:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我始终没叫他帮我找我妈\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So I didn't ask his help to look for my mom at all{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.81,0:27:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后来我…后来我跟了老大\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Later on I... later on I found myself a chief{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.98,0:27:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他们…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But they...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.95,0:27:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们说…只是去抢劫\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They just said to rob{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.13,0:27:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有意思…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why not...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.39,0:27:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还想走\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come back here!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.29,0:27:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Still want to run?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.63,0:27:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,按著她！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hold her down!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.63,0:27:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不如打电话勒索她家吧\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why don't we phone her home for blackmail?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.90,0:27:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,电话号码呀？三八！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Phone number? Bitch!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.80,0:27:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放我走！放我们走呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Please let me go! Let us go{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.57,0:27:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you saying?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.74,0:27:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,电话号码英文怎么说？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What's phone number in English?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.04,0:27:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们不知道吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You don't know?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.54,0:27:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我哪知道！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How should I know!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.54,0:27:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神经病！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Damn!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.41,0:27:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈的！没电话号码怎能勒索？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Shit! How can we blackmail them without the phone number?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.25,0:27:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全都是饭桶！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}All useless shit!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.55,0:27:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来，有便宜要占！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on! Might as well!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.55,0:27:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么搞的？你怎会按不住她的？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What the hell! Why can't you hold her down?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.09,0:27:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会认出我们的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They two will recognise us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.89,0:27:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打死他！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Kill him!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.59,0:27:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来！拿着，打他！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on! Hold this, beat him!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.39,0:27:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈的！来呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Shit! Come on!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.30,0:27:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,警告你们，人人有份，都得打几下\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm warning you, no one can stay out of this{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.34,0:27:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁要不动手，我就打死他\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll kill whoever doesn't beat them{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.64,0:28:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过来，拿着！打他，打他呀\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on, hold this! Hit him, hit him!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.08,0:28:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没想到会在宝马山闹出了命案\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't expect Braemar Hill to cost lives{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.59,0:28:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你呢？十二年前你干了什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What about you? What did you do 12 years ago?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.16,0:28:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很痒啊\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Very itchy!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.23,0:28:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自摸三番，糊了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What an easy win!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.10,0:29:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么，你看你女儿！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What? Look at your daughter!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.70,0:29:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你死丫头，你给我下来呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Damn you, get down!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.61,0:29:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,死丫头，你表姨父你也搞…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You damned girl, you even seduced your own uncle...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.35,0:29:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈…别再打了…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom... stop...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.88,0:29:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你死丫头，我没你这个女儿， 你给我滚！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Damn you, I don't want a daughter like you. Get out!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.99,0:29:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.79,0:29:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不要你这个死丫头，你给我滚\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't want a daughter like you. Get out{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.13,0:29:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我先穿好衣服呀\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me put my clothes back on first{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.90,0:29:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还想穿什么衣服？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You still need your clothes?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.93,0:29:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你给我滚，走啊\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Get out, out!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.70,0:29:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈…开门…开门呀…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom... open the door... open the door!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.44,0:29:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈！别这样，让我进去吧\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom! Don't be like that, let me in!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.34,0:29:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.87,0:30:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所谓“臭坑出臭草”\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Stinky grass only grows out of a stinky pot{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.97,0:30:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由中国政府钦点的筹委\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Organising Committee appointed by the Chinese government...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.94,0:30:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再由这些筹委决定了四百人的推委\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}decided on the 400 members of the Election Committee{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.08,0:30:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来来去去都是这些人提名我们的特首\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's always the same group of people nominating our Chief Executive{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.68,0:30:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,试问那些参选人的候选政纲…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}May I ask how can candidates' election platforms...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.35,0:30:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么才能跳出中国政府规定的框框？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}avoid the limitations determined by the Chinese government?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.35,0:30:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一句“臭坑出臭草”\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}His Stinky grass only grows out of a stinky pot{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.49,0:30:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,骂了整个立法局和身兼推委的议员\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}insulted both the Legislative Council and Councillors on the Election Committee{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.96,0:30:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么解释？主席，请你定断\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How do you solve this, Mr Chairman? Please determine{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.03,0:30:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱忠勤议员，你愿不愿意收回 你刚才说的话？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Councillor, do you wish to withdraw your statement?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.60,0:30:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会收回\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}No, I don't!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.37,0:30:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为话已经说出来了，我不能收回\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I've said it, I can't take it back{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.77,0:30:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,誉玲就是找了这个人帮我们\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's him who Yue-ling got for us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.98,0:30:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你不收回的话，请你马上离开\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If you won't, please leave immediately{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.58,0:30:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天不用再回来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}And not to return today{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.39,0:31:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个“臭坑出臭草”行不行的？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Will this stinky pot work?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.63,0:31:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再臭也是个议员嘛！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}No matter how stinky he is, he's still a Councillor{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.76,0:31:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们寄了那么多信，只有他肯帮我们\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Among all the letters we sent, he's the only one willing to help{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.34,0:31:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，犯人家属全来了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The prisoners' families are all here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.97,0:31:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请他们进来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Bring them in{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.48,0:31:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进来吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come in!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.85,0:31:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来介绍一下，这位是粱议员\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me introduce the Councillor, Mr Leung{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.45,0:31:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们全靠他的了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We all depend on him{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.98,0:31:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家好！        粱议员你好！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hi, everyone! Hi, Councillor!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.05,0:31:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们全靠你了，你一定要帮我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We all depend on you, you must help us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.05,0:31:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一定会尽力帮忙的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll try my best.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.83,0:31:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一张是等候发落的犯人名单\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is the list of detained prisoners{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.46,0:31:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们在家属一栏签个名就行了， 传给大家吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sign your name in the Next of Kin box. Pass it over!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.60,0:31:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，你要帮帮我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Councillor, you must help me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.04,0:31:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我儿子和不认识的人打架\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My son fought with someone he didn't know{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.57,0:31:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一句“看什么” ， 结果便杀了人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Just because he said, What are you looking at me for? It cost some lives{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.41,0:32:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没钱为儿子打官司\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I have no money for a lawsuit{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.18,0:32:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法律援助署的律师说…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Legal Aid lawyer said...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.38,0:32:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,判等候发落，最多关十年罢了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It was a maximum of 10 years for detention at Her Majesty's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.22,0:32:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我就叫他认谋杀罪算了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So ljust asked him to plead guilty{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.16,0:32:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁知道认了便不能上诉了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So he did and couldn't appeal{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.29,0:32:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说怎么办？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What should I do?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.43,0:32:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，我弟弟也是这样\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My younger brother was like that too, Councillor{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.96,0:32:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他十三岁就辍学了，在车行里当学徒\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He quit school at 13, and became an apprentice in a garage{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.57,0:32:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁知天天碰到小混混，问他要钱\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The street kids asked him for money every day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.44,0:32:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看他总不交钱给家里就骂他\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He didn't bring home any money, so I yelled at him{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.24,0:32:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一天他回车房拿锯子\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}One day, he went back to the garage for a saw,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.41,0:32:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是用来自卫的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}which was for self-defence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.54,0:32:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁知道…谁知道弄成这样！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Nobody expected it to turn out like this!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.38,0:32:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我先说！我弟弟叫小发\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me speak first! My younger brother is called Fatt{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.25,0:32:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一天他在吃宵夜\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}One evening he was having midnight snack{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.49,0:32:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,旁边的人盯著他，老是盯著他\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Some people kept staring at him{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.99,0:32:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他火了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He got agitated{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.22,0:32:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人家那边凶得要命，人多势众\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Those people were a gang and they were yelling{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.93,0:32:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他就坐计程车走\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He left in a taxi{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.76,0:32:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是在车上愈想愈气，结果就跑回去\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and felt more and more agitated. So he returned...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.03,0:32:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冲进人家的厨房，拿了刀到处乱砍\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}forced his way into the kitchen, grabbed a chopper and swung it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.37,0:32:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事情不是我弟弟惹起来的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My young brother didn't start it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.64,0:32:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们家的人脾气非常暴躁\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My family members are all very hot tempered{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.14,0:33:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道了以后，正好手上拿着钥匙， 就打了过去\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}When I learned about it, ljust grabbed my keys and hit him...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.61,0:33:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,差点弄瞎了他！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and almost blinded him!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.41,0:33:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要知道我们住在木屋区\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We live in a wooden shack district, you know{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.32,0:33:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我老妈天天骂人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom scolds us everyday{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.25,0:33:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老爸在五金店工作苦，回家就发脾气\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Dad has a tough time working in a hardware store. So he loses his temper at home{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.70,0:33:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爸，你看我多棒！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, Dad! Ain't I good?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.16,0:33:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一口就把药粉吃光了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I finished the powder in one mouthful{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.60,0:33:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小忠真乖！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Good boy, Siu-chung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.77,0:33:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爸，电影要开始了，还不走就迟到了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Dad, come on! We'll be late forthe movie!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.34,0:33:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起，我还要去开会！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sorry! I still have to go to a meeting{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.21,0:33:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我回家是要拿点儿东西，不能陪你了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}ljust came home to pick something up, can't go with you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.21,0:33:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明明说好的，现在又说开会，你骗人！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You promised and now you have to go to a meeting! You lied!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.48,0:33:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小忠！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Siu-chung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.62,0:33:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不理你了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Leave me alone!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.52,0:33:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小忠，你出来！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come out, Siu-chung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.92,0:33:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要冷静一下\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I want to calm down{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.26,0:33:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,秀仪，你陪小忠去看吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why don't you go with him, Sau-yee?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.79,0:34:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,儿子说看“给我一个爸” 是应该爸爸陪的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Our son said his Dad should go with him to watch Kolya{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.33,0:34:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天的会是很重要的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The meeting is very important{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.34,0:34:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪次你不是这么说？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What else is new?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.87,0:34:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我《妇女协会》的会就不重要？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So my Women's Association meeting is not important?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.24,0:34:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我早跟你说了，我今天要开会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I told you I had a meeting to attend today{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.35,0:34:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你总说你有理想\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You always say you were idealistic{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.48,0:34:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,光是你有，我就没有！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So only you are and I'm not!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.32,0:34:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将来你做了救世主，儿子却不认你了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Your son denies you when you become a Saviour{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.33,0:34:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,誉玲！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yue-ling!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.67,0:34:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你做我的助手，不怕丢了工作吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you not worried about losing your job helping me here?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.41,0:34:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我把工作辞掉了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I quit{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.11,0:34:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,辞掉了？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You did?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.47,0:34:46.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的！不用担心\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes! Don't worry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.25,0:34:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直都想做一点事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I always wanted to do something...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.01,0:34:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不为了钱，也不为了生活\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}not forthe sake of money or living{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.42,0:34:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在机会来了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Here is my chance{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.35,0:34:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我明天陪你到赤柱（监狱）好不好？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Can I go with you to Stanley (prison) tomorrow?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.79,0:34:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天有议员要来吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}A Councillor is coming here today?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.86,0:34:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的！机灵点\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah! Be smart!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.63,0:35:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，你好！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hi, Councillor!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.49,0:35:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hi!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.70,0:35:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我姓潘，是这里的辅导员\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Poon, I'm an adviser here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.50,0:35:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好！这是张誉玲小姐，我的助手\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hi! This is Miss Cheung Yue-ling, my assistant{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.23,0:35:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好！        你好！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hi! Hi!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.57,0:35:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里有六个HMP（等候英女皇发落） 犯人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I advise all 6 prisoners detained at{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.64,0:35:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全是由我辅导的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Her Majesty's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.17,0:35:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在已经安排了他们跟你见面了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They have arranged to meet with you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.74,0:35:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这边请！        谢谢你！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This way, please! Thank you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.34,0:35:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,张小姐，行了，今天有特别安排\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's OK, Miss Cheung, a special arrangement today{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.11,0:35:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这边请！        谢谢！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This way, please! Thank you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.15,0:35:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿Sir，今天开放式？这样子来探访！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's Open Day today, Sir? So many visitors!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.72,0:35:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人家是议员，不是你妈！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What we have here today is a Councillor, not your mom!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.06,0:35:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，张小姐\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Councillor, Miss Cheung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.32,0:35:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我以前所念课程拿到的文凭\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Here are the diplomas I received forthe courses I studied{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.56,0:35:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们看一看！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Take a look!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.40,0:35:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在正念公开大学社会系的 一个函授课程\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm now taking a correspondence course in Sociology at the Open University{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.93,0:35:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对现在的年青人都有理论 和实践的认识\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So I have both theoretical and practical knowledge fortoday's youngsters{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.01,0:35:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在监狱推荐我做了监狱社工， 去辅导所有犯人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I was recommended as the adviser here to advise all prisoners{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.38,0:35:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有青年中心也替我出过书\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Also, a youth centre helped publish my books{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.01,0:36:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在…现在只想做一件事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}There's only one thing... I want to do now{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.49,0:36:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想知道究竟还要在这里困多久？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I want to know how much longer I have to be stuck here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.03,0:36:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很想出去！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I really want to get out of here!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.33,0:36:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想以过来人的身份告诉所有年青人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I want to tell all the youngsters about my experience{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.61,0:36:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,千万别犯法！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Never violate the law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.58,0:36:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很希望你们能帮我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I really wish you could help me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.95,0:36:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭，里边在拍教育电视吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Are they filming an educational TV program in there, Ming?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.85,0:36:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是陈永发吧？        是的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you Chan Wing-fatt? Yes!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.65,0:36:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什么话要说？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What have you got to tell me?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.46,0:36:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,据我所知，长囚会每两年 就复检我们的案子\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}As far as I know, the Long Term Detention Review Committee (LTDRC) reviews my case every 2 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.23,0:36:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的档案又重又厚\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My file is thick and heavy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.36,0:36:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们找秘书看了这些档案\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They get a secretary to go over my file,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.40,0:36:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,写几句结论\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}write a conclusion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.37,0:36:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,复检委员就只凭这几句结论 决定我们的命运\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and that is just how the Committee members determine my fate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.51,0:36:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根本不公正、不客观、不准确\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Neither just, objective, nor accurate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.84,0:37:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种官僚制度便决定了我们的命运\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is the bureaucratic system that determines ourfate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.75,0:37:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望我刚才的一番话有效吧\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I hope what I said was useful{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.82,0:37:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是教师\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm a teacher{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.66,0:37:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我发现他比我的学生还聪明\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I discovered he's even smarterthan my students{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.19,0:37:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另外，他们的法律知识比很多 立法局议员还多\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Also their legal knowledge is more detailed than many Councillors'{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.26,0:37:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那当然了！ 这是他们的切身问题\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Certainly! That is what most concerns them{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.17,0:37:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们天天研究法律，讲人权、讲自由\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They study law day and night, talk about human rights and freedom{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.04,0:37:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是却从来没想过受害人家属的感受\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yet they neverthink about what the victims' families feel{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.18,0:37:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们两个，进来！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come in, you two!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.58,0:37:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那边\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Go overthere{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.82,0:37:47.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是粱议员，这是张小姐\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is the Councillor, this is Miss Cheung{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.66,0:37:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是黄育\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm Wong Yuk{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.29,0:37:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是张有铭        你好！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm Cheung Yau-ming Hi!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.50,0:37:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起，该这一份才对\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sorry! It should be this file{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.04,0:37:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}OK!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.58,0:38:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sit!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.58,0:38:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，我能不能说几句？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung, may I say something?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.98,0:38:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然可以！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}By all means!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.48,0:38:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，我宁愿香港跟大陆一样\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'd rather Hong Kong was the same as the Mainland{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.49,0:38:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.16,0:38:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样枪毙我就算了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So I can be shot once and for all,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.43,0:38:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我妈用不著每次来都哭\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and my mom won't need to cry every visit{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.16,0:38:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这里会关押到什么时候！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know how long I will be detained here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.24,0:38:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在没死是因为家里有妈妈\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I stay alive simply because I have a mom at home{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.24,0:38:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,万一我妈有什么事的话\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If something happened to her,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.31,0:38:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会自杀的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'd commit suicide!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.79,0:38:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,孩子们挺乖的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The kids are pretty well behaved{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.55,0:38:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.99,0:38:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,张有铭很少说话\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Cheung Yau-ming rarely talked{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.16,0:38:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是那些等候发落的犯人之中…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He's the only one detained at Her Majesty's pleasure...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.99,0:39:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯一没亲人为他争取确定刑期的一个\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}who has no family to fight on his behalf for a defined term,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.80,0:39:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且十几年来家里人也没来看过他\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}as his family has never come to visit in the past 10 years or so{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.74,0:39:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也曾经帮他找过他家里人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I once helped him to get in touch with his family{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.64,0:39:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很想找到他妈妈\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He wants to look for his mom so badly too{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.21,0:39:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是找不到\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But no luck!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.18,0:39:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宝马山双尸案，当年这案子 真的非常轰动\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Braemar Hill case really shook the whole society that year{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.92,0:39:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新闻不停播放，报纸也登了不少\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The news was on airfrom time to time, and newspaper reports{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.59,0:39:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭说他是被逼犯罪的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming said he was forced to commit the crime{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.66,0:39:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信他，当时他那么小，才十几岁\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I believe him. He was so young, just a teenager{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.70,0:39:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些年来他那么努力读书\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He's been studying very hard these years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.17,0:39:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是想能早点出狱，重新做人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He plans to get out early and turn over a new leaf{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.08,0:39:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你跟他非亲非故，为什么要帮助他？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why do you want to help him? You are not related to him!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.45,0:39:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't know!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.28,0:39:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能小时候没人关心我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Probably because no one cared for me in my childhood{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.76,0:40:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很明白没人关心自己的感觉\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I fully understand those feelings{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.73,0:40:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在木屋区长大\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I grew up in a wooden shack district{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.13,0:40:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那儿的环境很差\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The environment was really bad there{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.87,0:40:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们用的电都是从路灯那儿偷来的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The power supply was stolen from the streetlights{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.80,0:40:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很容易发生火灾\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Fires occurred very easily{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.54,0:40:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,火灾发生就很难逃命\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and it was very hard to escape{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.81,0:40:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我妈带我从大陆来这儿\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My mom brought me from the Mainland;{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.58,0:40:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来了之后她完全变了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}since then she changed completely{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.12,0:40:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,脾气很坏\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}She became very bad tempered,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.02,0:40:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天天怕这个、怕那个\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and was afraid of this and that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.99,0:40:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你呢，你为什么帮他们？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What about you? Why are you helping him?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.33,0:41:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欧洲人权法庭已裁定不定期 押后判刑是违法的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The European Human Rights Court ruled that indefinite detention is illegal{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.57,0:41:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么要等女皇判决呢？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why must there be at Her Majesty's pleasure?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.70,0:41:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乃因为案件特殊\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Because in special cases,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.07,0:41:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不能由法庭和法官去判决\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}it is not forthe court and judge to set the sentence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.34,0:41:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该改由非司法机构或非司法人士来判决\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The sentence is set by non-judiciary people or organisations{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.15,0:41:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就是说筹钱打官司也是没用的了？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In that case, there's no point in raising money for a lawsuit?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.25,0:41:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,港督只有四个多月时间\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Governor only has about 4 months left here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.69,0:41:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这二十三个青少年犯是殖民地 法律制造出来的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}These 23 young offenders were created by colonial law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.66,0:41:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,殖民政府撤离香港前有责任解决这件事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The colonial government must deal with them before leaving{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.80,0:41:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,万一回归前…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What if the Hong Kong-British government...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.13,0:41:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,港英政府没裁定明确刑期，那怎么办？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}hasn't determined the sentence before the Handover?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.77,0:41:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据基本法第四十八条\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}According to article 48 of the basic law,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.04,0:41:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特区行政长官有权赦免任何犯人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}the Chief Executive of the SAR has the right to grant amnesty{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.48,0:42:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是回归后“等候英女皇发落”的裁决\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But Detained at Her Majesty's pleasure might change to...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.68,0:42:07.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能就会改为等候特首发落 之类的判刑吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Detained at the Chief Executive's pleasure afterthe Handover,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.52,0:42:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是说变相重复裁决同一罪名\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}which means double jeopardy forthe same crime{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.72,0:42:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是不符合人权法的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That is against the human rights law!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.33,0:42:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生！我来这儿开会，看到你太好了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung! I came here to consult, it's so nice to bump into you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.27,0:42:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你太太催你签离婚书\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Your wife urges you to sign the divorce papers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.17,0:42:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你告诉她，我不签！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Tell her I won't!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.81,0:42:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁啊？小忠？什么事啊？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Who is it? Siu-chung? What's the matter?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.12,0:42:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你生日我记著了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I rememberyour birthday!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.26,0:42:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过你生日那天爸要开会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But I have to go to a meeting on your birthday{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.96,0:42:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,改天我买个大冰淇淋蛋糕给你好吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll buy you a big ice cream cake sometime, OK?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.00,0:42:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别生气了，好吧？拜拜！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't get upset! All right? Bye!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.64,0:43:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈咪，我来帮你好吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom, may I help?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.91,0:43:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小忠，小心！别把妈咪的东西弄脏\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Be careful, Siu-chung, don't dirty Mom's things{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.81,0:43:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听话，自己玩去！别碍著妈做事好吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Be a good boy, go play yourself, OK? Mom's busy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.88,0:43:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乖，快去！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on, go!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.19,0:43:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对…记得！今天开会，是的， 我会准时到的time\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah... I remember! We have a meeting today. Yes! I'll be there on time{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.13,0:43:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你把人找齐，把文件准备好，对…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You go collect everyone, and get the papers ready. Right!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.80,0:43:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爸…今天是星期日， 你陪我出去玩啊！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Dad! Lt's Sunday today, go play with me!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.67,0:43:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一会儿再跟你说，就这样吧，拜拜！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll call you back, OK! Bye!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.20,0:43:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爸今天要开会，不能陪你了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Dad has to go to a meeting today, and can't play with you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.97,0:43:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下星期好吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How about next week?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.28,0:43:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么这样子？将来妈咪跟你 离婚之后，我才不跟你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How can you do this to me? I won't go with you when Mom divorces you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.62,0:43:48.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么跟儿子说这些话？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why did you tell our son things like this?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.85,0:43:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么？儿子无权知道我们之间的事吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why not? Hasn't our son the right to know what's happening between us?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.69,0:43:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们之间有什么事？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What is happening between us?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.99,0:43:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我尊重你做的事，你也要尊重我， 对不对？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I respect what you do, and so you must respect me too, right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.79,0:43:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说来说去都是那一套，我懒得理你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't be bothered, you just keep saying the same thing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.26,0:43:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要赶去中环示威呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I must rush to Central for a demonstration!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.16,0:44:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你照顾一下儿子吧，别去示威了， 好吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why don't you spend some time with our son? Don't go, will you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.03,0:44:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you talking about?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.97,0:44:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我最近见了二十几个青少年犯\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I've met about 20 young prisoners lately{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.44,0:44:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有点害怕呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm really worried!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.98,0:44:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怕就好了，儿子没你份的吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Good foryou! Isn't he your son too?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.82,0:44:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小忠！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Siu-chung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.78,0:44:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈咪要去做事，听爸的话，知道吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom has some work to do. Do what Dad will ask you to, all right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.92,0:44:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}All right!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.49,0:44:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈咪拜拜\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Bye, Mom!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.84,0:44:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小忠！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Siu-chung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.25,0:44:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,干什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.38,0:44:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟爸去开会好吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Will you go with me to the meeting?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.32,0:44:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不去！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}No!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.58,0:44:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开完会我请你吃饭\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll eat out afterthe meeting{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.55,0:44:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要吃牛扒跟香蕉船！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I want steak and a banana split!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.96,0:44:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想吃什么都行\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Whateveryou want{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.09,0:45:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是先要吃药，你吃了没有？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But you must take your medicine first. Have you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.69,0:45:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吃了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.40,0:45:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吃了？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You have?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.21,0:45:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小忠你出来！爸有话问你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Get out, Siu-chung! I want to ask you something{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.05,0:45:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你明明没吃，为什么说吃了？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You haven't taken it; why did you say you had?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.82,0:45:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说谎是不对的，你知道吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Lying is wrong, you know that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.06,0:45:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把手拿出来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Put your hand out{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.67,0:45:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爸打你，你生爸的气吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Dad hit you. Are you mad at me?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.08,0:45:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还疼不疼爸？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you still love Dad?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.83,0:46:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还疼不疼爸？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.90,0:46:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不说话…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You're silent...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.77,0:46:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是说你不疼爸了，对吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}means you don't, right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.94,0:46:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Right!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.79,0:46:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么不疼爸？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.99,0:46:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从来不陪我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You never spend time with me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.91,0:47:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最近很多人需要爸帮忙\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Many people need Dad's help lately{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.48,0:47:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我答应你，我帮完他们以后…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}When I finish helping them, I promise...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.82,0:47:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我天天陪你上街好吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll take you out every day, OK?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.54,0:47:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起！你代我签吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sorry, can you sign for me? I'm illiteracy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.70,0:47:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们先吃啊！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You go ahead!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.27,0:47:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请结帐！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The bill, please!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.11,0:47:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走了？再坐一会儿嘛！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you going? Stay for a while!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.88,0:47:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位，我跟保安司谈过\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Gentlemen, I've talked to the Secretary for Security{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.92,0:47:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说等候英女皇发落的犯人…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He said prisoners who are detained at Her Majesty's pleasure...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.35,0:47:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要留给将来特区政府的行政长官处理\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}are to be managed by the Chief Executive of the SAR{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.66,0:47:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我早说英国人是靠不住的了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I told you the British were unreliable{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.06,0:47:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我都说他们在推卸责任的了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}As I said, they are disregarding their responsibilities{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.69,0:47:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回归以后，公安随时会抓那些人 去枪毙的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The police will shoot the kids any time afterthe Handover{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.80,0:47:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎…么…办呢我儿子…？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What will happen to my son?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.13,0:48:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,求求你！救救我儿子！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I beg you! Save my son!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.31,0:48:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,婆婆你别哭了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't cry, Madam! You make me feel lost{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.61,0:48:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要去港督府抗议\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We want to have a demonstration at the Governor's House{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.48,0:48:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抗议是需要的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}A demonstration is necessary{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.21,0:48:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你要明白，我们现在为重犯请愿\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But you must understand that we are now appealing for serious offenders{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.75,0:48:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不仅是挑战官僚架构\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Not only are we challenging the bureaucratic structure,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.25,0:48:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走到街上去就是挑战整个社会 对囚犯憎恨的态度\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}but we're also challenging society's resentful attitude towards prisoners{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.52,0:48:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们想成功，你们就一定 要坚持到底\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So if we want success, you must be persistent to the end{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.66,0:48:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们马上搞一个街头签名运动\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll organise a signature campaign on the street{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.73,0:48:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,签名收集够了就递交港督\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}When enough signatures are collected, we'll submit them to the Governor{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.73,0:48:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那可不行，我不能让别人知道 我儿子在坐牢\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}No! I can't let people know my son is in jail{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.67,0:48:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不行，我跟别人说儿子在深圳 做生意罢了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Me neither! I told people my son runs a business in Shenzhen{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.41,0:48:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,香港四分之一的家庭都有人坐牢\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}A quarter of Hong Kong families have members in jail{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.11,0:48:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们站出来的话，也许有人会 同情我们的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If we stand out, we might gain sympathy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.41,0:48:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是很多人都像我从前那样\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The thing is,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.15,0:48:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,装著很憎恨犯罪的人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}many people pretend to hate criminals like us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.92,0:48:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好让人家以为自己跟犯人没关系嘛！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So that others think they have nothing to do with criminals{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.19,0:48:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要是记者在我脸上打格子，那我就答应\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll do it only if reporters conceal my face{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.22,0:48:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果怕被别人认出来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If you're worried people will recognise you,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.09,0:48:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你们戴帽子好了、戴墨镜好了、 蒙著脸也可以\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}wear a hat, sunglasses, or coveryourface{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.80,0:49:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是示威游行的人一定要多， 一定要够\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But many people must participate in the demonstration. We must have enough{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.30,0:49:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,婆婆，你那么爱哭， 不如对著记者哭吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You enjoy crying so much! Why don't you cry in front of the reporters?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.40,0:49:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,惠珍，这次的请愿行动， 由你负责联络家属\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Take charge of liaison with the families forthe demonstration, Wai-chun!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.98,0:49:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好啊！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}OK!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.98,0:49:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也去查一下资料， 看对他们有帮助没有！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll go check the information to see if it's any help{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.25,0:49:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.42,0:50:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,站住…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.59,0:50:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帮忙抓住她…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hold her down...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.49,0:50:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,救命啊…放我走！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Help... Let me go.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.06,0:50:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抓住她的手…    干什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Grab her hands! What are you doing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.06,0:50:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抓住她…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Grab her hands!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.80,0:50:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh my God...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.05,0:50:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,张开她的腿！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Open her legs!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.41,0:50:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抓著她的手！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Grab her hands!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.62,0:51:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别吵呀，死老外！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop yelling, jerk!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.97,0:51:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杀害我儿子和他女朋友的人该被判死刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Whoever did this to my son and his girlfriend deserve a death penalty.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.98,0:51:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们的行为连禽兽都不如\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They'd be put to death, they're animals, they shouldn't be walking around!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.20,0:51:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快出发了，怎么誉玲还没来？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We're going soon, why isn't Yue-ling here?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.77,0:51:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道！打电话给她也没人听\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't know! I called her and there was no answer{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.81,0:52:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不等她了，我们出发吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We are not waiting for her, let's go!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.55,0:52:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小心别涂错！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Be careful, don't get it wrong!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.71,0:52:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里好像还欠一点儿！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It doesn't seem OK here!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.85,0:52:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要很鲜艳的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Make it more colourful{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.49,0:52:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭，书上这个May day， 是什么意思？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What does May day here in the picture mean, Ming?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.26,0:52:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是May day ，是Mayday\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's not May day, it's Mayday{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.39,0:52:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你在海上遇险，要求救， 是救命的意思\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If you are in danger at sea and need help. It means Help!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.60,0:52:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayday     救命救命的意思\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mayday means help{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.63,0:52:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个管用呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is useful!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.50,0:52:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayday      我们也要求救呀\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Right! We need mayday{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.71,0:52:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在是本港新闻\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Now, the local news{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.11,0:52:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,立法局议员粱忠勤…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Legislative Councillor Leung Chung-ken...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.58,0:52:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天陪同多名仍然等候英女皇 发落的犯人家属…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}went with many families of prisoners detained at Her Majesty's pleasure...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.38,0:52:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由铜锣湾轩尼斯道游行至港督府…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to march from Hennessey Rd in Causeway Bay to the Governor's House{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.42,0:52:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为青少年犯争取确定刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}demanding determination of juvenile offenders' sentences{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.46,0:52:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英国人应当承担责任！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Britain is responsible!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.42,0:52:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青少年犯也有人权！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Juvenile offenders have rights too!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.73,0:52:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人权不容践踏！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Human rights are not to be stepped on!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.17,0:52:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英国人应当承担责任！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Britain is responsible!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.00,0:52:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青少年犯也有人权！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Juvenile offenders have rights too!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.44,0:53:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,争取马上确定刑期！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Fight for immediate determination of sentence!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.18,0:53:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青少年犯不是垃圾！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Juvenile offenders are not trash!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.12,0:53:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人权不容践踏！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Human rights are not to be stepped on!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.42,0:53:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,争取马上确定刑期！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Fight for immediate determination of sentence!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.56,0:54:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿勤，留点儿时间给我们吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Save some time for us, Ken!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.30,0:54:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,搞这种犯人的案子，吃力不讨好\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Dealing with criminals of this kind will get you nowhere{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.40,0:54:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱忠勤，保安司说什么就什么嘛\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Do whateverthe Secretary for Security says, Ken!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.97,0:54:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还搞那么多事干什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why bothers doing all this?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.77,0:54:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快下车（不能过渡回归的议员）了， 那么多事要做\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We're off the train soon (replaced afterthe Handover). We've much to do!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.21,0:54:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实我们每个都收过那些信\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In fact, we all received letters like that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.51,0:54:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,犯人总喜欢叫人帮他们减刑的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Prisoners always want people help to reduce their sentences{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.45,0:54:16.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们又不是法官\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We are not judges,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.71,0:54:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,何况香港60％的市民都赞成死刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and 60% of Hong Kong people want the death penalty{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.82,0:54:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你帮重犯说话似乎不很符合民意哪！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You're siding with serious criminals; it doesn't go with public opinion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.29,0:54:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何为了二十几个人而 开罪三百万选民呢？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why irritate 3 million voters for the sake of about 20 people?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.29,0:54:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我明白你的意思\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I understand what you're saying{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.86,0:54:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我始终想做我认为对的事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But I still want to do what I think is right{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.60,0:54:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位市民，一群曾经被法庭判为\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Fellow citizens, a group of juvenile offenders,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.27,0:54:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“等候英女皇发落”的青少年犯\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}who the court sentenced to be detained at Her Majesty's pleasure,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.30,0:54:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在要求香港政府本著人道及人权立场\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}ask the HK Government to determine their sentences as soon as possible...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.27,0:54:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽快给他们明确的刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}from humanitarian and human rights standpoints{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.48,0:54:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好让他们可以计划未来，重新投入社会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So that they can plan theirfutures and re-enter society{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.81,0:54:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请各位市民过来签名，支持他们\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Please come and sign your name to support them,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.55,0:54:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使他们早日得到刑期，谢谢大家！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to enable their sentences to be determined as soon as possible.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.99,0:55:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“请各位市民过来签名，支持他们，“\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Please come and sign your name to support them,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.32,0:55:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽快给他们明确的刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to enable their sentences to be determined as soon as possible{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.59,0:55:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使他们能够准备未来，重新融于社会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to enable them to prepare forthe future and re-enter society{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.30,0:55:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请各位市民过来签名\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Please come and sign your name{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.07,0:55:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，我是你的支持者\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Councillor, I support you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.80,0:55:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.00,0:55:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我什么都支持你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I support you in everything you do{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.74,0:55:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是帮杀人犯我就不支持了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But not when you support murderers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.14,0:55:18.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生，你有所不知！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You don't understand, Mister!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.64,0:55:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些青少年犯罪的时候\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Those teenagers were not mature...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.48,0:55:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,心智还未成熟，不很清楚 自己在干什么！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}when they committed crimes. They didn't know what they were doing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.85,0:55:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,何况现在他们在牢里无了期地等\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's torture forthem...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.95,0:55:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是很磨人的事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to wait endlessly in jail{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.42,0:55:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最可怜的是由于他们没有确定刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The worst is, they can't appeal...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.56,0:55:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根本没有办法上诉\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}without determined sentences{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.79,0:55:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对他们很不公平！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's extremely unfain'to them!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.90,0:55:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，你这是什么议员？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What kind of Councillor are you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.33,0:55:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最近一群青年放火烧掉一间卡拉OK， 死了很多人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Recently some kids set fire to a karaoke bar and many people died{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.40,0:55:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎能放那些青少年犯呢？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How can you set those juvenile offenders free?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.77,0:55:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们曾经给政府写过很多信\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I sent many letters to the Government...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.77,0:55:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,询问有关等候英女皇发落的青少年犯\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to ask if the young offenders who are detained at Her Majesty's pleasure...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.47,0:55:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到底他们能否在主权移交前 得到合理刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}could have their sentences determined before the Handover{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.21,0:55:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但政府总在打官腔\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But the government always gave bureaucratic answers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.45,0:55:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多信写了去政府那里\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Many letters have been sent to the government{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.75,0:56:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,呸！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Shit!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.25,0:56:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你做什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you doing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.35,0:56:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你做什么？别捣乱！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you doing? Stop fooling around!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.19,0:56:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是什么人？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Who are you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.03,0:56:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么人都不关你事！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}None of your business!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.29,0:56:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别打了…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.93,0:56:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,停手！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop... calm down...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.91,0:56:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据最新的社会调查指出\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}According to the latest social survey...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.38,0:56:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,香港有42％中学生认为没有人 可以说心里话\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}42% of high school students have nobody to discuss their problems{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.02,0:56:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,34％的中学生认为父母不了解他们…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}34% of those whose parents don't understand them...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.75,0:56:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们吵什么？坐一边去吧， 我还要做生意呢！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Move aside! I have business to do!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.90,0:56:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要不是你拦著我，我一定揍那混蛋\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I would give him a good lesson if you didn't stop me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.17,0:56:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我实在忍无可忍了，你们两怎么搞的？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't stand you people anymore, what did you think you were doing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.90,0:56:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在和平请愿示威， 你两却在跟人打架？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We were having a peaceful demonstration, and you two fought?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.07,0:56:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们有没有想过市民会怎看我们？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you ever care about how people would look at us?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.12,0:57:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起！我不该那么大声的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sorry, I shouldn't have raised my voice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.29,0:57:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过我真想告诉你们\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But I'm telling you,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.72,0:57:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们真的很不对！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}you were very wrong!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.06,0:57:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，你根本不用说对不起， 是他们不对！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung, you don't need to say sorry. They were wrong!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.50,0:57:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员和我们非亲非故\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung isn't related to us at all{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.87,0:57:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他没义务帮我们的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He has no obligation to help us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.93,0:57:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上次游行我的样子见了报以后， 人人就怕了我们！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My picture was in the news in the last demonstration. Now they stay away!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.44,0:57:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只要嗓门大了点儿\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It was just that my voice was a bit loud{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.91,0:57:32.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们看！这厨子立即就把菜刀 牛肉刀都收起来了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Look at this chef! He hid his choppers right away{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.38,0:57:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们一定要克制自己\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So we must restrain ourselves{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.85,0:57:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要不然就救不了家里人了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Otherwise we won't be able to save ourfamilies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.25,0:57:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,算了！惠珍，别动气了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's OK, Wai-chun! Don't lose your cool{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.95,0:57:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找到誉玲了吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Have you located Yue-ling?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.75,0:57:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有！我打了很多电话给她， 都没人听\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}No! I called her many times, there was no answer{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.84,0:58:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爸爸就会骂我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Dad scolded me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.91,0:58:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了最后，我也没有找他帮我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't ask him to help after all{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.69,0:58:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么打这小孩呢？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why are you beating this boy?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.86,0:58:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我教儿子关你什么事？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm teaching my son a lesson. What has it got to do with you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.39,0:58:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是这样教儿子的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That's no way to treat your son!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.89,0:58:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这样打他，他将来会坐牢的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If you beat him like that, he'll go to jail in the future{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.80,0:58:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐牢也不关你的事！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}His going to jail has nothing to do with you either!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.93,0:58:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不听话…     我不敢了…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't you dare not to listen to me... I won't dare any more{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.84,0:58:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别再打了，他是你儿子，你知道吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop! He's your son, don't you know?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.24,0:58:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么事？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What's going on?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.54,0:58:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿Sir，他打他儿子！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sir, he's beating his son!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.51,0:58:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么打孩子？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.71,0:58:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我教我儿子\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I was teaching my son a lesson{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.74,0:58:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,教儿子也不能打，你还绑著他？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That's not an excuse. You tied him up?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.88,0:58:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快放了他，不然告你虐待儿童\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let him go or I'll press charges against you for child abuse{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.63,0:59:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很久没见了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Long time no see!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.13,0:59:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hi!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.84,0:59:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你弄伤了手？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Your hand's injured?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.84,0:59:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.81,0:59:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没事吧？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you OK?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.74,0:59:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生说你病了，我很担心\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung said you were sick, I was worrying about you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.55,0:59:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看你那么久没来， 还以为你出了什么事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You haven't come for a long time, I thought something happened to you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.35,0:59:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为我做了那么多的事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You have done so much for me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.69,0:59:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次你病了，我都不能出去看你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You were sick, and I couldn't even pay you a visit{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.00,1:00:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,求求你，让我进去！我还想再看看他\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Please let me go back in, I still want to see him!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.44,1:00:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不行，出来了就不能再进去！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}No! You can't go back in once you've come out!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.74,1:00:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下星期再来好了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come again next week!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.94,1:00:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.34,1:00:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别叫了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop shouting!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.61,1:00:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sorry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.25,1:00:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sorry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.43,1:00:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sorry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.48,1:01:02.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，影印机又坏了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung, the photocopier has broken down again{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.62,1:01:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明天找人来修一下吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Get someone to fix it tomorrow!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.06,1:01:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，如果再做犯人案子的话 我想辞职了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung, I'll resign if we continue with the criminals' case{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.50,1:01:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的亲戚朋友知道我帮犯人做事 都在说我的不是！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My relatives gossiped about me when they learned I work for criminals!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.43,1:01:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对啊！再说，也快回归了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah! The Handover is coming,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.97,1:01:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到时候你也没议员当了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}by then you won't be a Councillor anymore{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.94,1:01:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不如多做一点反对临时立法会的事 不是更好吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Won't it be better if we work against the provisional Legislative Council?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.18,1:01:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,何况犯人是没有投票权的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Offenders have no right to vote anyway!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.15,1:01:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们两个干什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you two doing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.72,1:01:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些英国人把小孩像垃圾 一样的扔在一边\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Those British throw these kids aside like trash{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.55,1:01:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是对的吗？那没违反人权吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Is it right? Doesn't it violate human rights?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.95,1:01:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做事不能光计较后果，该做的就要做！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You can't calculate the result, you should do what you must do!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.20,1:01:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你回来干什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you doing here?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.40,1:01:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们最缺人的时候你就不见了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You disappeared when we needed helping hands the most{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.37,1:01:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有你我照样会帮他们的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I will still help them without you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.97,1:02:01.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看了宝马山命案的资料后，我很害怕\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I was very afraid after reading about the Braemar Hill case{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.98,1:02:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不是早就知道自己在帮什么人的吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Didn't you know what people you were helping in the first place?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.25,1:02:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,色彩强一点\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Use stronger colour{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.32,1:02:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,色彩多一点\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}More colourful!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.14,1:02:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青少年犯不是垃圾！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Juvenile offenders are not trash!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.28,1:02:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,争取马上确定刑期！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Fight for immediate and specific sentences{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.51,1:02:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青少年犯也有人权！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Juvenile offenders have rights too!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.09,1:02:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭，对不起！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sorry, Ming!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.72,1:02:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我曾经想放弃你，不再帮你了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I once thought of giving you up, not helping you any more{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.89,1:02:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请你原谅我！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Please forgive me!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.26,1:02:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我看到宝马山双尸案的资料的时候\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}When I read about the case of the Braemar Hill couple{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.17,1:03:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我真的很害怕\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I was really frightened{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.24,1:03:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不相信在我眼前的你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't believe the person I see now...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.94,1:03:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,曾经做过那么凶残的事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}did such a brutal thing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.58,1:03:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实我比你也好不了多少\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Actually, I'm no betterthan you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.15,1:03:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也是一个犯过罪的人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I once committed a crime too{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.35,1:03:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,十二年前，我想杀了我的表姨母\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I wanted to kill my Aunt 12 years ago{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.16,1:03:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是我没被人抓到\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Only I was not arrested{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.26,1:03:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以现在还能自由自在的到处去\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So I'm still free to go anywhere{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.53,1:03:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然我知道没借口可以掩饰我们 曾经犯过的罪\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Although I realise there is no excuse for our crimes,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.94,1:03:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我又很明白你童年时 所受过的伤害\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I fully understand your childhood suffering{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.94,1:03:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭，我不知道你会怎么想\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know what's in your mind, Ming{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.34,1:03:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我觉得纵使时光可以倒流\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But I feel that if we could go back into the past,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.28,1:03:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不想再来一次\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I wouldn't want it to happen to me again{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.85,1:03:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我怕自己会再犯同样的错\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Because I'm afraid I would still make the same mistake{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.49,1:03:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要求尽早确定刑期！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We demand specific sentences as soon as possible!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.86,1:04:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青少年犯也有人权！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Juvenile offenders have rights too!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.33,1:04:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要求尽早确定刑期！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We demand specific sentences as soon as possible!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.67,1:04:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反对无了期监禁！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We object to endless imprisonment!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.14,1:04:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要求尽早确定刑期！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We demand specific sentences as soon as possible!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.38,1:04:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反对无了期监禁！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We object to endless imprisonment!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.45,1:04:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青少年犯也有人权！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Juvenile offenders have rights too!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.55,1:04:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反对无了期监禁！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We object to endless imprisonment!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.16,1:04:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要求尽早确定刑期！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We demand specific sentences as soon as possible!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.56,1:04:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等一下，粱议员有话要说\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Wait! Mr. Leung has something to say{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.67,1:04:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位，任何触犯法律的人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ladies and gentlemen, anyone who violates the law...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.54,1:04:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都该受到合理的惩罚\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}should receive reasonable punishment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.51,1:04:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是今天我们的香港\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But nowadays in Hong Kong,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.88,1:04:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们高度强调法治和人权\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}we emphasise law and order, and human rights{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.28,1:04:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却竟然忽略了二十三个等候英女皇 发落的青少年犯\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yet we have ignored 23 young criminals detained at Her Majesty's pleasure,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.32,1:04:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无限期地监禁他们\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and imprisoned them indefinitely{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.52,1:05:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱议员，这里的一些剪报都 是跟问题青少年有关的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}All these newspaper clippings are about juvenile delinquents{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.29,1:05:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为值得帮助这些问题青少年吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you think they are worth helping?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.06,1:05:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我个人认为问题青少年是 问题社会的产物\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I personally think that juvenile offenders are products of a sick society{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.03,1:05:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们老说青少年这不好、那不好\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We keep saying that teenagers are bad in this orthat way{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.13,1:05:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,追求名牌、挥霍无度、乱搞男女关系\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They are vain, waste money, and have sex all the time{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.80,1:05:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是有很多成年人可能忘了…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But probably many adults might have forgotten that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.74,1:05:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们也曾经历过心智不成熟的成长阶段\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}we went through these immature stages while growing up too{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.81,1:05:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们一方面埋怨一代不如一代、 青少年愈来愈不长进\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}On one side we complain about teenagers become more and more careless{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.58,1:05:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是另方面却在制造一个堕落的世界\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But on the other, we are creating a world of corruption...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.75,1:05:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,引诱青少年做坏事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to seduce teenagers into bad ways{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.69,1:05:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得这样很不公平，也很荒谬\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I find this ridiculous and very unfair{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.42,1:05:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,立法会主席赶你走的时候 干么你不坚持呢？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why didn't you insist when the LegCo Chairman expelled you, Mr. Leung?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.59,1:05:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为“臭坑出臭草” 这句话有问题吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Was your phrase Stinky grass only comes from a stinky pot problematic?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.69,1:05:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在殖民议会上\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You were the first one on record who got chased out...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.79,1:05:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你开创了第一次指出不民主选举 而被赶离场的纪录\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}after pointing out the undemocratic election at a colonial meeting{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.60,1:05:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你该为自己的勇气而骄傲， 坚持不离场的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You should have been proud of yourself and insisted on staying{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.80,1:05:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么主席叫你走，你就走？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why did you do what the Chairman said?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.10,1:05:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得今天不是讨论这问题的适当时候\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't think it's appropriate to discuss this mattertoday{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.43,1:06:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,港督彭定康复核了二十三名 被判等候英女皇发落…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Governor Patten reviewed the 23 cases detained at Her Majesty's pleasure...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.60,1:06:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而仍然未确定刑期的犯人个案后\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}yet they still haven't been given specific sentences{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.87,1:06:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,决定释放四名被押刑期过长的囚犯\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and he decided to free 4 who had been jailed fortoo long{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.00,1:06:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又为两名被押超过十五年的 犯人确定刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He also confirmed the sentences of 2 who had been jailed for over 15 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.71,1:07:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其余的个案就交给将来的特区政府处理\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The rest of the cases are to be handed over to the SAR government{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.48,1:07:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你，粱先生，我终于得到了 二十六年的刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you, Mr. Leung! I finally got confirmation of 26 years' imprisonment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.61,1:07:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不必客气！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You're welcome!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.12,1:07:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,二十六年！刑期比成年犯还重\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}26 years! The sentence is even longerthan for adult criminals{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.79,1:07:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有了刑期就可以申请假释\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He can apply for parole now{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.82,1:07:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,扣除假期，再捱一个多月， 就可以放出去了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}After holidays, he can be out in a month{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.36,1:07:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不对呀！这样就是说…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is not right! That means...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.36,1:07:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,政付被迫要判重一点儿\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}the government was forced to decide on longer sentences{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.83,1:07:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果轻判了，关久了不知道\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If not, then if someone was already jailed for longerthan he should be,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.43,1:07:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那白关了的日子怎样赔？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}how could the government pay him back?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.14,1:07:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也好，有刑期代表有希望\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's good, with a given sentence, there is hope{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.87,1:07:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们二十三个人争取确定刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}23 of us fought for determination of sentence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.81,1:07:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彭定康只是处理了五个赤柱 （监狱）的案子\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}And Chris Patten only settled 5 of the Stanley (Prison) cases{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.91,1:07:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,石壁（监狱）这边，只有国良\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Over here in Shek Pik (Prison), only Kwok-leung got it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.48,1:07:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,剩下我们十七个怎么办呢？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What about the 17 of us?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.12,1:07:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彭定康是一个政客\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Chris Patten is a politician{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.79,1:07:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要十分，通常他只会给你三分\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You want 10, usually he'll just give you 3{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.96,1:07:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回归前我会尽最大的努力\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll try my very best before the Handover{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.59,1:07:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会尽量帮你们的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll help the best I can{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.83,1:07:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,犯人也有人权！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Prisoners have human rights too!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.30,1:08:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人权不容践踏！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Human rights are not to be stepped on!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.07,1:08:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,立即确定刑期！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Determine the sentences immediately!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.34,1:08:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,香江电台记者何慕诗现在 还继续在立法局…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ho Mo See of Radio Television Heung Kong now continues her report...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.28,1:08:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现场报导回归前最后一次 立法局会议的情况\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}on the last meeting before the Handover, outside the Legislative Council{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.48,1:08:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么还没提到我们\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why didn't they mention about us?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.82,1:08:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到现在为止，会议已经开了 超过十个小时s\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So far, the meeting has been going on for over 10 hours{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.05,1:08:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现场所见，多位议员都开始有疲态\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Many Council members at the meeting are beginning to look tired{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.29,1:08:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在立法会门外，有多个团体静坐抗议\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Many groups are holding sit-in protests outside the Council{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.96,1:08:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们认为临时立法会是非法的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They think the Provisional Legislative Council is illegal{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.13,1:08:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在休息之前，议员刚刚辩论完 香烟条例草案\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Council members have just finished a debate on the tobacco bill... before the break{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.83,1:08:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿发，什么时候才会轮到我们？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}When will it be ourturn, Fatt?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.83,1:08:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我哪儿知道！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How should I know?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.10,1:08:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算轮到，你们也不是马上就可以走的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Even so, you people won't be free in the next second!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.27,1:08:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟著是辩论保安科所提交的长期 监禁刑罚覆检条例草案\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Next is the Security Branch review of the long-term imprisonment bill{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.48,1:08:41.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席，各位议员\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Chairman, fellow Councillors{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.64,1:08:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,首先，为提供一个刑期复检…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}First of all, in orderto provide a sentence review...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.78,1:08:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说到我们了，大家安静\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's ourturn! Quiet, everyone!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.05,1:08:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们建议把原来长期囚禁覆检委员会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We suggest confirming the LTDRC...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.39,1:08:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,确立为法定机构\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}as a legal organisation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.49,1:08:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基于等候英女皇发落 这项判决的性质和目的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Due to the nature and purpose of detained at Her Majesty's pleasure,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.09,1:09:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,裁决为酌情终身监禁\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The verdict is now discretionary life sentence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.97,1:09:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等候英女皇发落和酌情终身\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We can't equate detained at Her Majesty's pleasure and discretionary life sentence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.67,1:09:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,此两事根本不能相提并论\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}because they are two totally different things{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.11,1:09:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“酌情终身”本来就有终身的含意\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Discretionary life sentence virtually means a life term{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.21,1:09:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是“等候英女皇发落” 却只是等待发落\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But detained at Her Majesty's pleasure is just waiting to be sentenced{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.91,1:09:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等待一种宽大的刑罚\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Waiting for a generous penalty...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.92,1:09:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绝对没有终身的含意\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}absolutely does not imply a life term{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.95,1:09:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果未满十八岁的青少年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If teenagers under 18...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.99,1:09:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也受到同样有终身含意的刑罚\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}also sufferthe penalty of an implied life term,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.89,1:09:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那青少年犯和成年犯到底有什么分别？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}then how does a juvenile offender differfrom an adult criminal?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.66,1:09:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法庭一直都把十八岁以下 该判死刑的犯人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Criminals under 18 with the death penalty...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.00,1:09:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,判为等候英女皇发落\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}were detained at Her Majesty's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.37,1:09:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很明显是不想把青少年犯和成年犯 用同一方法处理\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Obviously young offenders should not be handled the same way as adults{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.27,1:09:46.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再说，就算是成年犯判了死刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Even if an adult is sentenced to death,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.28,1:09:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,港督亦例必改判为终身监禁\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}the Governor always changes it to life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.25,1:09:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果现在把等候英女皇发落 等同酌情终身的话\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If we now equate detained at Her Majesty's pleasure with discretionary sentence for life,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.62,1:09:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们岂不是兜了个大圈子？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}don't we just go back to where we started?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.55,1:09:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么要这么做呢？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Why are we doing this?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.95,1:09:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们是不是要将青少年犯心智不成熟\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you want to ignore the very reason of...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.49,1:10:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个那么值得考虑的因素一笔勾销？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}young criminals' immaturity, which is so much worth considering?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.99,1:10:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请大家看看你们面前的那份犯罪记录\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Please take a look at the criminal record in front you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.47,1:10:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,囚犯编号四七六二八\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The prisoner's number is 47628{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.47,1:10:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长囚会在一九九二年一月复检他的案子\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The LTDRC reviewed his case in January, 1992{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.81,1:10:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他犯罪的时候只有十五岁\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He was only 15 when the crime was committed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.15,1:10:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以前没有任何犯罪记录\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Before that he was clean{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.68,1:10:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长囚会对他在监狱工作的表现 和学业成绩…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The LTDRC complimented...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.98,1:10:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都有很高的评价\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}his studies and his performance in jail{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.25,1:10:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长囚会鼓励他继续发奋图强和改过自新\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They encouraged him to keep working hard and make a new life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.39,1:10:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是一直到今天\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But up to today,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.99,1:10:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他仍然没有一个确定的刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}he still hasn't had his sentence determined{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.60,1:10:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,试问他怎样发奋图强、怎样改过自新？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How can he keep working hard and make a new life?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.97,1:10:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们这个所谓文明社会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How can our so-called civil society...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.60,1:10:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,竟可那么不人道地继续监禁一个 想改过的年青人！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}continue to jail a youngster who wants to correct himself like that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.64,1:10:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这公平吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Is it fair?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.78,1:10:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们所谓的酌情终身\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Your so-called discretionary life sentence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.74,1:10:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实只是一个逃避责任、明哲保身\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}is just an excuse to avoid responsibility, to keep your hands clean{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.65,1:11:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和无限期监禁他的一个籍口\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and leaving him to indefinite imprisonment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.28,1:11:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一九九三年四月\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In April, 1993,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.85,1:11:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,立法局修改法例，废除死刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}the Legislative Council amended the law to repeal the death penalty{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.69,1:11:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,任何年龄的人只要谋杀罪名成立\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Anybody of any age, as long as he is guilty of homicide,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.96,1:11:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就一律被判终身监禁\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}will be sentence for life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.13,1:11:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在这条草案，是根据法理和法律 程序起草的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Now that this bill has been drafted, based on legal procedures and processes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.33,1:11:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绝对没有忽视人道精神\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The humane spirit has absolutely not been ignored{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.27,1:11:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于危害社会的杀人犯来说\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}As for murderers who harm society,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.40,1:11:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“酌情终身”已经是最人道的判决\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}discretionary life sentence is the most humane sentence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.44,1:11:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法律有责任保护社会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Law has the responsibility of protecting society{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.11,1:11:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们绝不能轻易放过危害社会的杀人犯\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We can't easily let go of them{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.31,1:11:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然我们已经废除了死刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Although we repealed the death penalty{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.28,1:11:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是在你们心目中\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But in your heart,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.65,1:11:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“杀人偿命”这观念仍然根深蒂固\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}the view of A life for a life is still deeply held{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.02,1:11:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果真是这样，我想奉劝一句\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If this is really the case, let me give you a piece of advice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.79,1:11:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们这个铁面无私和公正严明的政府\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That our government of justice and principle,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.49,1:11:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有我们这群尊贵的议员\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}as well as our noble Councillors,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.46,1:11:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要再玩把戏，不要再愚弄那群孩子了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}stop playing tricks and stop fooling those boys{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.96,1:11:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么玩把戏？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What trick?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.63,1:11:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,律政司已经把长囚会界定为法律机构了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Attorney General already made the LTDRC a legal organisation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.37,1:11:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不是改进吗？我们没必要 在这问题上浪费时间\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Isn't this progress? We shouldn't waste any more time on this issue{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.80,1:11:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得我们没有浪费时间\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't think so{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.77,1:11:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果“等候英女皇发落”\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}If detained at Her Majesty's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.07,1:11:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被理解为“酌情终身监禁”的话\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}is understood as discretionary life sentence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.04,1:12:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那不仅在法律应用上是错误的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It is not only wrong in terms of legal usage,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.15,1:12:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后果也非常严重\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}but the result is also very serious{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.25,1:12:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当年，根据刑事诉讼条例第七十条\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That year, according to the Criminal Procedure Ordinance, Article 70{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.88,1:12:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于法官不能判青少年重犯死刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}since the judge couldn't sentence young criminals to death,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.85,1:12:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以才判为等候英女皇发落\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}he sentenced them to be detained at Her Majesty's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.26,1:12:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里还有一个个案\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Here's another case{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.46,1:12:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成年犯五八三零四犯了杀人罪， 法庭判了他死刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}An adult criminal 58304 committed murder, and was sentenced to death{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.06,1:12:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长囚会建议他改判终身\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The LTDRC recommended life imprisonment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.00,1:12:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后来便改判为三十年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Later his sentence was changed to 30 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.80,1:12:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,此人入狱后又杀人，又判死刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He committed murder again in jail, and was sentenced to death again{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.57,1:12:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长囚会又建议改判他三十四年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}And the LTDRC again recommended a sentence of 34 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.11,1:12:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,扣除了假期，他实际上 只需坐二十二年牢\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}After deducting holidays, he's actually required to spend 22 years in jail{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.28,1:12:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我们的小孩已经坐了十几年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But the boys have already been jailed for more than ten years...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.61,1:12:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在换来的只是“酌情终身监禁”\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and are just in exchange for discretionary life sentence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.65,1:12:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是什么逻辑？！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What kind of logic is this?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.65,1:12:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法治社会讲求理性\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}A society of law and order demands rationality{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.15,1:12:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绝不能因为一个人感情用事 而伤害整个社会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That cannot be harmed simply because someone becomes emotional{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.29,1:12:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理性？你那些只是麻木不仁的理性\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Rationality? What you said was an unfeeling kind of rationality{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.49,1:12:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们只说惩罚、惩罚、再惩罚\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What you all say is just penalty, penalty, still penalty{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.89,1:12:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,惩罚可以解决所有问题吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Can penalties solve all problems?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.13,1:12:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在不是在清洁香港\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We are not cleaning up Hong Kong now{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.87,1:12:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不能把我们看成是垃圾的 东西扔在一边\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We can't just put something we considertrash aside...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.30,1:13:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就以为能解决一切问题了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and expect all problems to be solved{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.31,1:13:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱忠勤，你没头没脑的 风头出够了没有？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Haven't you attracted enough attention, Leung Chung-ken?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.44,1:13:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保安司的条例虽然不太好\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Although the Security Branch ordinances are not so great,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.35,1:13:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但总比没有的好\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}they are betterthan none{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.78,1:13:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,政府这次也算不错的了， 肯马上起草草案回应你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The government did well this time by drafting the bill immediately{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.12,1:13:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通过就算了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Just accept what we passed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.95,1:13:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们还有十多小时便要下车了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We won't be Councillors anymore in 10 hours or so{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.22,1:13:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道你放心把这条草案交给 临时立法会处理吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you comfortable handing this bill to provisional Legislative Council?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.53,1:13:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由保安科提议的长期监禁 刑罚复检条例草案\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}After all Councillors voted,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.77,1:13:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,经议员投票后已有了结果\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}the result of the Security Branch Life Term Review Bill has come out{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.74,1:13:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,立法局以多数票通过了 由保安科提案的…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Life Term Sentence Review Bill suggested by the Secretary Branch...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.25,1:13:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长期监禁刑罚复检条例草案\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}were passed in the Legislative Council by a majority vote{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.25,1:13:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并否决了粱议员的六项修订动议\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}And the 6 amendments moved by Councillor Leung Chung-ken were vetoed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.87,1:14:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,犯人也有人权！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Prisoners have rights too!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.10,1:14:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人权不能践踏！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Human rights are not to be stepped on!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.41,1:14:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,立即确定刑期！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Determine the sentences immediately!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.64,1:14:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人权不容践踏！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Human rights are not to be stepped on!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.81,1:14:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,立即确定刑期！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Determine the sentences immediately!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.13,1:14:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,悲秋风 香江梦 家乡一切幻变中\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The wind of autumn sobs over Hong Kong's dream. Everything is changing at home{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.00,1:14:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,满腔热血失青春 各散西东命难同\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I lost my youth to my ardent faith. Ourfates differ as we part for separate destinations{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.84,1:14:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青年两代送 历劫半生命犹穷\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Two generations pass, half a lifetime goes, yet nothing is gained{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.75,1:14:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,秋来更思痛 谢了春花变残红\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Recalling the painful past in autumn, spring flowers wither, tarnished red{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.70,1:15:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本人董建华…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I, Tung Chee Wah...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.54,1:15:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,悲秋风 香江玫瑰梦 抚今追昔难舍中\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sobbing in the wind of autumn over Hong Kong's dream. Remembering the past, and it is difficult to forget{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.18,1:15:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那堪梦觉一朝空 难料沧桑别后容\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Nothing is left on awaking from the dream. I can't imagine how my home will look after all the hardships{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.08,1:15:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国家之情已伤痛 盼顾香江又重逢\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The feelings of our country are painful. Here I see Hong Kong again{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.92,1:15:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,飘零四海送 落拓他乡似条虫\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We wander around abandoned in another country like lost leaves{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.19,1:15:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们一定会重返立法会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We will return to the Legislative Council{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.93,1:15:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.57,1:15:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家先听我说，我们一定会回来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Say with me! We will return{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.41,1:15:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们一定会回来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We will return{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.45,1:16:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们一定重返立法会\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We will return to the Legislative Council{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.95,1:16:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们作为中国的一部分\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We, as part of China,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.96,1:16:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已经开始了一个民主奋斗的旅程\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}have already started the journey of fighting for democracy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.26,1:16:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个旅程不是容易的，是艰巨的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is not an easy journey. It is difficult{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.41,1:16:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在维多利亚港上空烟花灿烂\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Now Victoria Harbour sky is sparkling...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.28,1:16:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,引来接近四十万的市民 在维多利亚港两旁观赏\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}attracting almost 400,000 people in both sides of the harbourto see{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.01,1:16:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一起庆祝香港回归祖国\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Together celebrating Hong Kong's return to the motherland{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.75,1:16:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,誉玲，你记得吗？我曾经对你提过…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Remember, Yue-ling? I mentioned to you before...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.75,1:16:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我的牢房窗口看出去的那一座山\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}about the hill that I see from the window of my cell{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.46,1:16:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每次当我看著那山的时候\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Every time when I look at it,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.73,1:16:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我知道自己无法见到山后面 是怎样的时候\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}when I can't see what's behind it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.26,1:16:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就很害怕，觉得很恐怖\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I feel frightened, and am horrified{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.10,1:16:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前面我什么都看不见\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I can see nothing ahead of me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.34,1:16:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以后的日子，我真不知道怎么过\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know how to spend the rest of my life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.12,1:17:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把我们提出来后弄来一个“酌情终身”\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}After discussing our case, they gave us back discretionary life sentence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.49,1:17:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们等候英女皇发落变成等候特首发落\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Detained at HM's pleasure changed to detained at the CE's pleasure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.00,1:17:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那粱忠勤可靠得吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Is that Leung Chung-ken reliable?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.83,1:17:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你别这样说粱先生，他已经尽了力的了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't say that, he has already tried his best{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.57,1:17:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们搞一个监狱绝食抗议行动\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We're going to have a hunger strike{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.27,1:17:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去告诉记者！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You go and notify the press!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.74,1:17:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不要胡来，这样会影响法官 判你的刑期的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't lose control, it might affect the judge's sentence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.54,1:17:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生说虽然他已不是议员， 他还是会尽力帮我们\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung said, although he's no longer a Councillor{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.48,1:17:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不再会特别为我安排探监了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They won't have special arrangment for me to see you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.15,1:17:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以后我会减少来看你的时间\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I won't come so frequently...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.82,1:17:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想妨碍你家人的探期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}because I don't want to shorten yourfamily's visits{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.76,1:17:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实我妈年纪大了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In fact, my mom is old{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.46,1:17:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不希望她老远地跑来看我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't want herto exhaust herself coming here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.99,1:17:53.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她始终是你妈\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}She's your mom, after all{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.30,1:17:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,首席大法官会根据你的案子 和你多年的表现…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Chief Justice will suggest a sentence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.10,1:17:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给你一个建议服刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}based on your case and your performance in jail overthe past years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.37,1:18:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特首就会根据这个建议服刑期.\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Chief Executive will give you a determinate sentence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.30,1:18:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给你一个确定刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}based on the suggested sentence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.41,1:18:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不用担心，我会写求情信给特首的了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't worry! I'll send a letter of appeal to the Chief Executive{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.18,1:18:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.54,1:18:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，你们先走好了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll say goodbye here, Mr. Leung!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.61,1:18:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想在附近走一走\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I want to take a walk here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.51,1:18:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}OK!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.53,1:19:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭，我记得你向我提过\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming: I recalled the hill that you mentioned before{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.93,1:19:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你牢房窗口看出去的那一座山\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}the hill you can see from the window of your cell{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.70,1:19:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天我上山去替你看过了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I went up there to look on your behalf today{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.41,1:19:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,山后面是一个水塘，那儿的风景很美\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What's behind it is a reservoir with a very nice landscape{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.64,1:19:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望有一天你能到这儿来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I hope one day you can come...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.18,1:19:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看水塘美丽的景色\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to see the beautiful scenery of the reservoiryourself{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.17,1:19:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,司机，麻烦你，我要下车\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me get off, please!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.02,1:20:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找死也不要害我啊\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't give me trouble even if you want to kill yourself{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.02,1:20:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有没有看今天的报纸？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Have you read today's newspaper?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.05,1:20:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里，你看看这篇文章！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Here! Read this article{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.79,1:20:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生呢？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Where's Mr. Leung?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.62,1:20:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在里面\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In there!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.42,1:20:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生…  什么事？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung... Yes?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.39,1:20:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快，来看看这一则新闻\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come! Come and read this news{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.03,1:20:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当年宝马山双尸案受害者的家属\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The families of the Braemar Hill couple were in deep grief{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.06,1:20:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事隔十二年，他们已经 从仇恨中恢复过来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}After 12 years, their hatred has healed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.07,1:20:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还懂得宽恕别人， 写信给特首为当年的凶手求情\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and they can forgive; so they sent the CE a letter begging for mercy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.01,1:20:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这信对我们很有帮助\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This letter will help us a lot{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.51,1:20:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对啊！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.28,1:20:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这下我们有希望了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We have hope now this time!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.41,1:20:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好消息…好消息，快来！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Good news... good news, come on!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.85,1:21:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,关掉水龙头！来…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Turn the tap off! Come...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.18,1:21:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们看…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Look...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.99,1:21:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宝马山双尸案的事，那死者的父亲\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Braemar Hill couple's father...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.62,1:21:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,写信给政府，原谅小铭当年年少无知\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}wrote the government a letter, and forgave Ming's ignorance{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.56,1:21:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还求情说给他减刑\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He also begged for mercy and for reducing his sentence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.43,1:21:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太好了…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is just great...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.17,1:21:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别开心得太早，能马上出去吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't get excited too soon! You can't get out of here right now, can you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.57,1:21:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,起码会比你早！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll be out of here earlierthan you, at least!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.08,1:22:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈，我是你女儿誉玲\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom: This is your daughter, Yue-ling{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.91,1:22:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天我在报纸看到宝马山双尸案死者 家属的消息\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I read about the Braemar Hill couple's families in the newspapertoday{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.89,1:22:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们写信给特首为当年 杀害自己子女的凶手求情\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They wrote the CE a letter asking for clemency forthe murderers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.49,1:23:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想不到事隔十二年， 他们也学会了去宽恕一个罪人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't expect them to learn to forgive after 12 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.37,1:23:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而我竟然生了你十二年的气\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}While I have been mad at you forthe last 12 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.11,1:23:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有一个好朋友， 很小便没有见过他的亲母\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I have a good friend who hasn't seen his mom since he was very small{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.58,1:23:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很想找回他妈妈\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He wants to see his mom so much{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.82,1:23:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是他一生中最大的愿望\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That is the biggest hope in his life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.63,1:23:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而我…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}And I...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.66,1:23:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一个可以随时见到的妈妈\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}have a mother I can see any time,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.27,1:23:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是为何这许多年来 都没回家见你一面？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}yet all these years I didn't want to come home to see you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.95,1:23:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.49,1:23:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.76,1:24:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈，这条裙子都烂成这样了， 你还没扔？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This dress is so torn, and you haven't thrown it away, Mom?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.93,1:24:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你那么喜欢那条裙子\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You liked that dress so much{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.63,1:24:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怎么舍得扔掉呢？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How can I throw it away?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.08,1:24:54.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈，你不想知道这十二年我 都去了哪儿了？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't you want to know where I have been forthe past 12 years, Mom?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.82,1:25:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要想说的话，你早就说了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You'd have told me long ago if you wanted to{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.19,1:25:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要是不想说\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}There's no point in asking you...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.56,1:25:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我问你也没用！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}if you didn't{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.43,1:25:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,刚开始我在一家电子厂当工人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I first worked at an electronics factory{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.50,1:25:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后来我认识了一个比我 大二十几岁的男人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Then I met a man who was about 20 years olderthan me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.64,1:25:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他供我读书，就像当年表姨丈那样\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He paid for my school, just like my uncle{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.38,1:25:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道表姨丈的事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I realise what happened between me and uncle...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.32,1:25:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不知道啊！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't understand then!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.72,1:25:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小时候我很恨香港， 我不知道你为什么要带我来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I hated Hong Kong very much when you wanted to take me here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.03,1:25:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不想伤你的心\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't want to hurt you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.87,1:25:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是过去的事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But no one can change...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.87,1:25:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁也改变不了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}what happened in the past{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.28,1:26:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈，我现在挺好的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mom, I'm fine now{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.22,1:26:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在觉得…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}And now I feel...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.49,1:26:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们应该在一起住\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}we should live together{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.86,1:26:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还想…喝你煮给我的汤\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I also very much want to drink the soup you make!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.10,1:26:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Fine!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.33,1:26:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汤都凉了，赶快喝，来！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The soup is getting cold. Come on, drink quick!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.87,1:26:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多喝点…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Drink some more...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.50,1:26:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好喝！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Very delicious!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.14,1:26:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好喝！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Delicious!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.21,1:26:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多喝！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Drink more!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.45,1:26:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1998年7月\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}July of 1998{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.88,1:26:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐下！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sit!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.89,1:26:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天叫你们到这儿来…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We sent foryou today...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.49,1:26:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是因为你们的刑期报告已经来了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}because your sentence reports have arrived{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.99,1:26:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一会儿狱长会亲自向你们宣布\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The warden will announce them to you himself in a moment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.66,1:26:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进来！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Come in!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.10,1:26:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长官早！ 犯人到齐了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Good morning, Sir! The offenders are all here!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.97,1:26:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叫他们一个一个进来！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Send them in one by one!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.00,1:26:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,59827，进去！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}59827, go in!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.36,1:27:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别紧张，现在可不是判你们死刑！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't be nervous! You are not sentenced to death!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.88,1:27:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,60132，进去！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}60132, go in!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.17,1:28:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不可能！那些家伙在耍我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Lmpossible! Those guys are ripping me off!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.34,1:28:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们耍了我十几年了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They've been ripping me off for 10 years or so!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.07,1:28:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冷静点儿…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Calm down...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.34,1:28:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别闹…坐下…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't mess up! Sit!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.25,1:28:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要出去！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I want to get out of here!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.38,1:28:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们耍了我十几年了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You've been ripping me off for 10 years or so!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.08,1:28:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们耍了我十几年还没耍够吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Isn't it enough?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.52,1:28:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,董建华（香港特别行政区首长） ， 你这老糊涂！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Tung Chee Wah (Chief Executive of the SAR), you are senile!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.76,1:28:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,耍了我十几年了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Been ripping me off forten years!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.79,1:28:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放我出去…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me out...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.80,1:28:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么搞的？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't believe this!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.53,1:28:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下一个！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Next!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.53,1:28:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,67544，进去！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Go in, 67544!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.98,1:28:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,早，Sir！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Good morning, Sir!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.95,1:28:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sit!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.42,1:29:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,67544，终审庭首席大法官 看了你的个案\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}67544, Andrew Li of the Court of Final Appeal has looked into your case{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.66,1:29:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他建议你的最低必须服刑期是三十年\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He recommended a minimum term of 30 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.70,1:29:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特区首长董建华同意他的建议\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The CE, Tung Chee Wah, already agreed to his recommendation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.50,1:29:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这三十年里，你没有假期、没福利\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You will have no benefits or holidays in these 30 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.21,1:29:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也不能申请假释\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Neither can you apply for parole{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.71,1:29:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这段期间\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}During this period of time,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.38,1:29:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长囚会每两年会复检你的案子\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The LTDRC will review your case every 2 years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.88,1:29:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后再考虑你的实际刑期\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and will consideryour actual term{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.36,1:29:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想上诉\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I want to appeal{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.09,1:29:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是行政决定，你不能上诉\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You can't appeal since this is an executive decision{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.16,1:29:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你坚持，你可以试一试\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You may try if you insist{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.43,1:29:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你出去吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You may go!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.60,1:29:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,市民听说二十年、 三十年还以为很合理\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}People find 20 years or 30 years very reasonable{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.11,1:29:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他们不知道这些刑期 跟其他犯人不同\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What they don't know is these terms are different from other offenders{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.51,1:29:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无缘无故在刑期前面 加“最低”两个字\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The word minimum was added for no reason{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.65,1:29:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最低服刑期还不等于无限期再等？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Isn't minimum term the same as endless waiting?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.15,1:30:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,粱先生，电话\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Leung, phone!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.36,1:30:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Speaking...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.84,1:30:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.21,1:30:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,惩教署的辅导员打电话来\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Correctional Services Department called...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.98,1:30:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说那些孩子的情绪不好\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and said those kids became emotional{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.68,1:30:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以监狱这个月破例， 让家属无限次探监\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}So the prison is breaking the rules to allow unrestricted family visits{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.82,1:30:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小发，你的主意最多\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You have strong opinions, Fatt!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.86,1:30:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们这样子，怎么办？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}In a situation like this, what can we do?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.29,1:30:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找个人寻死，告诉政府我们的不满\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Pick someone to commit suicide, to tell the government we are unsatisfied{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.43,1:30:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我来吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll do it!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.14,1:30:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}No!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.60,1:30:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是监狱社工，监友需要你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You're a prison social worker, the inmates need you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.07,1:30:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我来！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me go!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.78,1:30:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要！想你妈哭死不成？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}No! You want to break your mom's heart?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.75,1:31:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以前是帮老大才进来的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I ended up here because I helped our Chief...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.18,1:31:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在希望为弟兄们做点事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Now I really want to do something foryou guys{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.92,1:31:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那也轮不到你呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You cannot do this!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.66,1:31:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里全靠你了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You're the only one left{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.99,1:31:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别争了，我刑期最长\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't fight, my term is the longest{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.00,1:31:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个抗议，让我来吧！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me take up the demonstration!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.75,1:32:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,致宝马山死者的家属\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}To the families of the Braemar Hill dead:{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.26,1:32:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是宝马山双尸案犯人之一，张有铭\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}This is one of the Braemar Hill offenders, Cheung Yau-ming{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.26,1:32:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道一句对不起无法补偿什么\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I understand one Sorry can't remedy anything{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.90,1:32:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我还是想对你们说一句：对不起\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But I still want to say, Sorry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.34,1:32:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当年我以为是跟著老大去抢劫\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}At the time, I thought I was just stealing with our Chief{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.21,1:32:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没想到会搞出了人命\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't expect it would take human lives{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.05,1:32:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当时老大给了我一根棍子\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}The Chief gave me a rod{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.35,1:32:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说随便打两下\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}He said I should strike with it a couple of times...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.98,1:32:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,表示人人有份\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to show that everybody's involved{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.42,1:32:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要不然就打死我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Otherwise he'd kill me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.16,1:32:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道犯了罪就该被惩罚\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I understand one should be penalised if he commits a crime{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.13,1:32:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我觉得这个最低必须服刑期 已经不是惩罚\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}but I find this minimum term of 30 years is already not a penalty,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.80,1:33:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是一种摧毁\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}it's a ruin{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.97,1:33:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是无论如何\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}However,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.00,1:33:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还是要感谢你们在承受 失去儿女的痛苦之后\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I still thank foryourforgiveness...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.54,1:33:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还能宽恕我、原谅我\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}after suffering the loss of children{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.08,1:33:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在我用我的性命\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Now I give my life...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.62,1:33:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亲自向你们谢罪！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}to apologise to you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.67,1:33:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭…为什么这样？小铭\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming... Why are you doing that? Ming!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.68,1:33:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭…别这样，小铭！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming... Don't! Ming!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.25,1:33:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要啊！小铭…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't, Ming!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.45,1:33:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要…不要…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't... don't...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.39,1:34:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭，你不要死！别这样！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming, don't die! Don't do that!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.60,1:34:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快放我出去！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me out!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.30,1:34:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人吗？救命啊！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Is anybody out there? Help!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.74,1:34:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.84,1:34:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊！小铭呀！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}God! Ming!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.61,1:34:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭…阿Sir，来呀，来人啊！阿Sir\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming... Sir, please! Sir! Sir!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.76,1:34:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,救命啊…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Help!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.32,1:34:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿Sir，小铭出事了，快点…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sir! Something's wrong with Ming, quick!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.16,1:34:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿发，小铭怎么样？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How's Ming, Fatt?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.40,1:34:40.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭怎么样？他怎么样了？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How's Ming?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.14,1:34:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,张有铭，你在干什么？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you doing, Cheung Yau-ming?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.94,1:34:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没事！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Nothing!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.95,1:34:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.39,1:35:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭，你没事了？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Ming, are you all right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.52,1:35:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没事！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm OK!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.76,1:35:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小铭，你没事了？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you OK, Ming?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.19,1:35:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你吓死我了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You scared the shit out of me!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.23,1:35:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没事！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm OK!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.33,1:35:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没事？没事？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you OK? OK?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.97,1:35:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们没事！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We're OK!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.41,1:35:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么样？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}How do you feel?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.51,1:35:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Sorry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.42,1:35:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你吓死我了，知道吗？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You know you scared me to death?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.36,1:35:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没事！没事就好了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}That's good!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.46,1:35:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别这样，小子！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't be like that, damn you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.83,1:35:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没错！不关你的事\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}It's not yourfault!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.51,1:35:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你吓死我了！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}You scared me to death!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.40,1:36:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}What's wrong?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.11,1:36:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我花了那么多精力和时间\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I spent so much time and energy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.05,1:36:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是帮不了他们\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}and still can't help them{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.32,1:36:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是起码可以让他们知道，世界上…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, at least they know...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.33,1:36:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有你这样的人关心他们，对吧？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}there are still people like you who care forthem, right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.31,1:37:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,誉玲，时间是公平的\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Yue-ling, time is just{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.95,1:37:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不论开心或不开心\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Whether happy or unhappy,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.89,1:37:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,始终都要过去\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}it will pass after all{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.16,1:37:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三十年，一万零九百五十天\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}30 years, 10,950 days{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.20,1:37:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我每天都会数著日子\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll count every day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.27,1:37:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,昨天我差点儿自杀了\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I nearly killed myself yesterday{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.51,1:37:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我没有死\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}But I didn't!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.18,1:37:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我相信\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Because I believe that...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.91,1:37:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,终有一天我会见到我的亲生母亲\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll meet my natural mother one day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.86,1:37:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会好好念书\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll study hard{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.66,1:37:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我答应你，我会考得最好\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I promise you, I'll get highest grades{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.27,1:38:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望在颁奖礼的时候\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I hope to see you...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.77,1:38:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以见到你\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}at the awards ceremony{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.14,1:38:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和你握手\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll shake hands then{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.88,1:38:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我答应你！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I promise you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.62,1:38:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你找谁？\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Who are you looking for?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.39,1:38:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好！我替朋友找他妈妈\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Hi! I'm helping my friend to look for his mother{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.92,1:38:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找妈妈？！\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}Looking for a mother?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.39,1:38:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我朋友叫张有铭，他妈妈叫潘有莲\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}My friend is called Cheung Yau-ming; his mother is called Poon Yau-lin{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.83,1:39:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不认识这个人\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know this person{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.50,1:39:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们以前就住在这儿\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}They used to live here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.73,1:39:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我这里有一张照片，你看看…\N{\fnTahoma\1c&H00FFFF&}I have a picture here, look...{\r}
